48class Aura;
49//
50// EFFECT HANDLER NOTES
51//
52// in aura handler there should be check for modes:
53// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL set
54// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK set
55// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK set - aura is recalculated or is just applied/removed - need to redo all things related to m_amount
56// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK - logical or of above conditions
57// AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_STAT - set when stats are reapplied
58// such checks will Speedup trinity change amount/send for client operations
59// because for change amount operation packets will not be send
60// aura effect handlers shouldn't contain any AuraEffect or Aura object modifications
61

382
383AuraEffect::AuraEffect(Aura* base, uint8 effIndex, int32* baseAmount, Unit* caster):
384 m_base(base), m_spellInfo(base->GetSpellInfo()),
385 m_baseAmount(baseAmount ? * baseAmount : m_spellInfo->Effects[effIndex].BasePoints), m_critChance(0),
386 m_oldAmount(0), m_isAuraEnabled(true), m_channelData(nullptr), m_spellmod(nullptr), m_periodicTimer(0), m_tickNumber(0), m_effIndex(effIndex),
387 m_canBeRecalculated(true), m_isPeriodic(false)
388{
389 CalculatePeriodic(caster, true, false);
390 CalculatePeriodicData();
391
392 m_amount = CalculateAmount(caster);
393 m_casterLevel = caster ? caster->getLevel() : 0;
394 m_applyResilience = caster && caster->CanApplyResilience();
395 m_auraGroup = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroup(GetId());
396
397 CalculateSpellMod();
398
399 // Xinef: channel data structure
400 if (caster)
401 if (Spell* spell = caster->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL))
402 m_channelData = new ChannelTargetData(caster->GetGuidValue(UNIT_FIELD_CHANNEL_OBJECT), spell->m_targets.HasDst() ? spell->m_targets.GetDst() : nullptr);
403}
404
405AuraEffect::~AuraEffect()
406{
407 delete m_spellmod;
408 delete m_channelData;
409}
410
411void AuraEffect::GetTargetList(std::list<Unit*>& targetList) const
412{
413 Aura::ApplicationMap const& targetMap = GetBase()->GetApplicationMap();
414 // remove all targets which were not added to new list - they no longer deserve area aura
415 for (Aura::ApplicationMap::const_iterator appIter = targetMap.begin(); appIter != targetMap.end(); ++appIter)
416 {
417 if (appIter->second->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
418 targetList.push_back(appIter->second->GetTarget());
419 }
420}
421
422void AuraEffect::GetApplicationList(std::list<AuraApplication*>& applicationList) const
423{
424 Aura::ApplicationMap const& targetMap = GetBase()->GetApplicationMap();
425 for (Aura::ApplicationMap::const_iterator appIter = targetMap.begin(); appIter != targetMap.end(); ++appIter)
426 {
427 if (appIter->second->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
428 applicationList.push_back(appIter->second);
429 }
430}
431
432uint32 AuraEffect::GetId() const
433{
434 return m_spellInfo->Id;
435}
436
437int32 AuraEffect::GetMiscValueB() const
438{
439 return m_spellInfo->Effects[m_effIndex].MiscValueB;
440}
441
442int32 AuraEffect::GetMiscValue() const
443{
444 return m_spellInfo->Effects[m_effIndex].MiscValue;
445}
446
447AuraType AuraEffect::GetAuraType() const
448{
449 return (AuraType)m_spellInfo->Effects[m_effIndex].ApplyAuraName;
450}
451
452int32 AuraEffect::CalculateAmount(Unit* caster)
453{
454 int32 amount;
455 // default amount calculation
456 amount = m_spellInfo->Effects[m_effIndex].CalcValue(caster, &m_baseAmount, nullptr);
457
458 // check item enchant aura cast
459 if (!amount && caster)
460 if (ObjectGuid itemGUID = GetBase()->GetCastItemGUID())
461 if (Player* playerCaster = caster->ToPlayer())
462 if (Item* castItem = playerCaster->GetItemByGuid(itemGUID))
463 if (castItem->GetItemSuffixFactor())
464 {
465 ItemRandomSuffixEntry const* item_rand_suffix = sItemRandomSuffixStore.LookupEntry(std::abs(castItem->GetItemRandomPropertyId()));
466 if (item_rand_suffix)
467 {
468 for (uint8 k = 0; k < MAX_ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_EFFECTS; k++)
469 {
470 SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* pEnchant = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(item_rand_suffix->Enchantment[k]);
471 if (pEnchant)
472 {
473 for (uint8 t = 0; t < MAX_SPELL_ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_EFFECTS; t++)
474 if (pEnchant->spellid[t] == m_spellInfo->Id)
475 {
476 amount = uint32((item_rand_suffix->AllocationPct[k] * castItem->GetItemSuffixFactor()) / 10000);
477 break;
478 }
479 }
480
481 if (amount)
482 break;
483 }
484 }
485 }
486
487 // custom amount calculations go here
488 // xinef: normal auras
489 switch (GetAuraType())
490 {
491 // crowd control auras
492 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE:
493 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_FEAR:
494 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN:
495 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT:
496 case SPELL_AURA_TRANSFORM:
497 m_canBeRecalculated = false;
498 if (!m_spellInfo->ProcFlags || m_spellInfo->HasAura(SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL)) // xinef: skip auras with proctriggerspell, they must have procflags...
499 break;
500 amount = int32(GetBase()->GetUnitOwner()->CountPctFromMaxHealth(10));
501 if (caster)
502 {
503 // Glyphs increasing damage cap
504 Unit::AuraEffectList const& overrideClassScripts = caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_OVERRIDE_CLASS_SCRIPTS);
505 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator itr = overrideClassScripts.begin(); itr != overrideClassScripts.end(); ++itr)
506 {
507 if ((*itr)->IsAffectedOnSpell(m_spellInfo))
508 {
509 // Glyph of Fear, Glyph of Frost nova and similar auras
510 if ((*itr)->GetMiscValue() == 7801)
511 {
512 AddPct(amount, (*itr)->GetAmount());
513 break;
514 }
515 }
516 }
517 }
518 break;
519 case SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_ABSORB:
520 case SPELL_AURA_MANA_SHIELD:
521 m_canBeRecalculated = false;
522 break;
523 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_DONE:
524 // Titan's Grip
525 if (!caster)
526 break;
527 if (GetId() == 49152 && caster->ToPlayer())
528 {
529 Item* item1 = caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(BASE_ATTACK);
530 Item* item2 = caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(OFF_ATTACK);
531
532 if (item1 && item2 && (item1->GetTemplate()->InventoryType == INVTYPE_2HWEAPON || item2->GetTemplate()->InventoryType == INVTYPE_2HWEAPON))
533 amount = -10;
534 else
535 amount = 0;
536 }
537 break;
538 default:
539 break;
540 }
541
542 // xinef: save base amount, before calculating sp etc. Used for Unit::CastDelayedSpellWithPeriodicAmount
543 SetOldAmount(amount * GetBase()->GetStackAmount());
544 GetBase()->CallScriptEffectCalcAmountHandlers(this, amount, m_canBeRecalculated);
545
546 // Xinef: Periodic auras
547 if (caster)
548 switch (GetAuraType())
549 {
550 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
551 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
552 // xinef: save caster depending auras, always pass 1 as stack amount, effect will be multiplicated at the end of the function by correct value!
553 if (GetBase()->GetType() == UNIT_AURA_TYPE)
554 amount = caster->SpellDamageBonusDone(GetBase()->GetUnitOwner(), GetSpellInfo(), amount, DOT, GetEffIndex(), GetPctMods(), 1);
555 break;
556 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
557 if (GetBase()->GetType() == UNIT_AURA_TYPE)
558 amount = caster->SpellHealingBonusDone(GetBase()->GetUnitOwner(), GetSpellInfo(), amount, DOT, GetEffIndex(), GetPctMods(), 1);
559 break;
560 case SPELL_AURA_DAMAGE_SHIELD:
561 if (GetBase()->GetType() == UNIT_AURA_TYPE)
562 amount = caster->SpellDamageBonusDone(GetBase()->GetUnitOwner(), GetSpellInfo(), amount, SPELL_DIRECT_DAMAGE, 0.0f, 1);
563 break;
564 default:
565 break;
566 }
567
568 amount *= GetBase()->GetStackAmount();
569 return amount;
570}
571
572void AuraEffect::CalculatePeriodicData()
573{
574 // xinef: save caster depending auras with pct mods
575 if (GetBase()->GetType() == UNIT_AURA_TYPE && GetCaster())
576 {
577 if (m_spellInfo->HasAura(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL))
578 m_pctMods = GetCaster()->SpellPctHealingModsDone(GetBase()->GetUnitOwner(), GetSpellInfo(), DOT);
579 else if (m_spellInfo->HasAura(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE) || m_spellInfo->HasAura(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH))
580 m_pctMods = GetCaster()->SpellPctDamageModsDone(GetBase()->GetUnitOwner(), GetSpellInfo(), DOT);
581 }
582
583 if (GetCaster())
584 SetCritChance(CalcPeriodicCritChance(GetCaster(), (GetBase()->GetType() == UNIT_AURA_TYPE ? GetBase()->GetUnitOwner() : nullptr)));
585}
586
587void AuraEffect::CalculatePeriodic(Unit* caster, bool create, bool load)
588{
589 m_amplitude = m_spellInfo->Effects[m_effIndex].Amplitude;
590
591 // prepare periodics
592 switch (GetAuraType())
593 {
594 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
595 // 3 spells have no amplitude set
596 if (!m_amplitude)
597 m_amplitude = 1 * IN_MILLISECONDS;
598 [[fallthrough]]; // TODO: Not sure whether the fallthrough was a mistake (forgetting a break) or intended. This should be double-checked.
599 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
600 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
601 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
602 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
603 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_FROM_CLIENT:
604 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_ENERGIZE:
605 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
606 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEALTH_FUNNEL:
607 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
608 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
609 case SPELL_AURA_POWER_BURN:
610 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY:
611 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
612 m_isPeriodic = true;
613 break;
614 default:
615 break;
616 }
617
618 GetBase()->CallScriptEffectCalcPeriodicHandlers(this, m_isPeriodic, m_amplitude);
619
620 if (!m_isPeriodic)
621 return;
622
623 // Xinef: fix broken data in dbc
624 if (m_amplitude <= 0)
625 m_amplitude = 1000;
626
627 Player* modOwner = caster ? caster->GetSpellModOwner() : nullptr;
628
629 // Apply casting time mods
630 if (m_amplitude)
631 {
632 // Apply periodic time mod
633 if (modOwner)
634 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(GetId(), SPELLMOD_ACTIVATION_TIME, m_amplitude);
635
636 if (caster)
637 {
638 if (caster->HasAuraTypeWithAffectMask(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HASTE, m_spellInfo) || m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_SPELL_HASTE_AFFECTS_PERIODIC))
639 m_amplitude = int32(m_amplitude * caster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED));
640 }
641 }
642
643 if (load) // aura loaded from db
644 {
645 m_tickNumber = m_amplitude ? GetBase()->GetDuration() / m_amplitude : 0;
646 m_periodicTimer = m_amplitude ? GetBase()->GetDuration() % m_amplitude : 0;
647 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_EXTRA_INITIAL_PERIOD))
648 ++m_tickNumber;
649 }
650 else // aura just created or reapplied
651 {
652 m_tickNumber = 0;
653 // reset periodic timer on aura create or on reapply when aura isn't dot
654 // possibly we should not reset periodic timers only when aura is triggered by proc
655 // or maybe there's a spell attribute somewhere
656 bool resetPeriodicTimer = create
657 || ((GetAuraType() != SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE) && (GetAuraType() != SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT));
658
659 if (resetPeriodicTimer)
660 {
661 m_periodicTimer = 0;
662 // Start periodic on next tick or at aura apply
663 if (m_amplitude)
664 {
665 if (!GetSpellInfo()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_EXTRA_INITIAL_PERIOD))
666 m_periodicTimer += m_amplitude;
667 else if (caster && caster->IsTotem()) // for totems only ;d
668 {
669 m_periodicTimer = 100; // make it ALMOST instant
670 if (!GetBase()->IsPassive())
671 GetBase()->SetDuration(GetBase()->GetDuration() + 100);
672 }
673 }
674 }
675 }
676}
677
678void AuraEffect::CalculateSpellMod()
679{
680 switch (GetAuraType())
681 {
682 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_FLAT_MODIFIER:
683 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_PCT_MODIFIER:
684 if (!m_spellmod)
685 {
686 m_spellmod = new SpellModifier(GetBase());
687 m_spellmod->op = SpellModOp(GetMiscValue());
688
689 m_spellmod->type = SpellModType(GetAuraType()); // SpellModType value == spell aura types
690 m_spellmod->spellId = GetId();
691 m_spellmod->mask = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].SpellClassMask;
692 m_spellmod->charges = GetBase()->GetCharges();
693 }
694 m_spellmod->value = GetAmount();
695 break;
696 default:
697 break;
698 }
699 GetBase()->CallScriptEffectCalcSpellModHandlers(this, m_spellmod);
700}
701
702void AuraEffect::ChangeAmount(int32 newAmount, bool mark, bool onStackOrReapply)
703{
704 // Reapply if amount change
705 uint8 handleMask = 0;
706 if (newAmount != GetAmount())
707 handleMask |= AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT;
708 if (onStackOrReapply)
709 handleMask |= AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAPPLY;
710
711 if (!handleMask)
712 return;
713
714 std::list<AuraApplication*> effectApplications;
715 GetApplicationList(effectApplications);
716
717 for (std::list<AuraApplication*>::const_iterator apptItr = effectApplications.begin(); apptItr != effectApplications.end(); ++apptItr)
718 if ((*apptItr)->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
719 HandleEffect(*apptItr, handleMask, false);
720
721 if (handleMask & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT)
722 {
723 if (!mark)
724 m_amount = newAmount;
725 else
726 SetAmount(newAmount);
727 CalculateSpellMod();
728 }
729
730 for (std::list<AuraApplication*>::const_iterator apptItr = effectApplications.begin(); apptItr != effectApplications.end(); ++apptItr)
731 if ((*apptItr)->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
732 HandleEffect(*apptItr, handleMask, true);
733}
734
735void AuraEffect::HandleEffect(AuraApplication* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply)
736{
737 // check if call is correct, we really don't want using bitmasks here (with 1 exception)
738 ASSERT(mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL
739 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT
740 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT
741 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_STAT
742 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SKILL
743 || mode == AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAPPLY
744 || mode == (AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT | AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAPPLY));
745
746 // register/unregister effect in lists in case of real AuraEffect apply/remove
747 // registration/unregistration is done always before real effect handling (some effect handlers code is depending on this)
748 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL)
749 aurApp->GetTarget()->_RegisterAuraEffect(this, apply);
750
751 // xinef: stacking system, force return if effect is disabled, prevents double apply / unapply
752 // xinef: placed here so above line can unregister effect from the list
753 // xinef: this condition works under assumption that effect handlers performs ALL necessery action with CHANGE_AMOUNT mode
754 // xinef: as far as i've checked, all grouped spells meet this condition
755 if (!aurApp->IsActive(GetEffIndex()))
756 return;
757
758 // real aura apply/remove, handle modifier
759 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK)
760 ApplySpellMod(aurApp->GetTarget(), apply);
761
762 // call scripts helping/replacing effect handlers
763 bool prevented = false;
764 if (apply)
765 prevented = GetBase()->CallScriptEffectApplyHandlers(this, const_cast<AuraApplication const*>(aurApp), (AuraEffectHandleModes)mode);
766 else
767 prevented = GetBase()->CallScriptEffectRemoveHandlers(this, const_cast<AuraApplication const*>(aurApp), (AuraEffectHandleModes)mode);
768
769 // check if script events have removed the aura or if default effect prevention was requested
770 if ((apply && aurApp->GetRemoveMode()) || prevented)
771 return;
772
773 (*this.*AuraEffectHandler [GetAuraType()])(aurApp, mode, apply);
774
775 // check if script events have removed the aura or if default effect prevention was requested
776 if (apply && aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
777 return;
778
779 // call scripts triggering additional events after apply/remove
780 if (apply)
781 GetBase()->CallScriptAfterEffectApplyHandlers(this, aurApp, (AuraEffectHandleModes)mode);
782 else
783 GetBase()->CallScriptAfterEffectRemoveHandlers(this, aurApp, (AuraEffectHandleModes)mode);
784}
785
786void AuraEffect::HandleEffect(Unit* target, uint8 mode, bool apply)
787{
788 AuraApplication* aurApp = GetBase()->GetApplicationOfTarget(target->GetGUID());
789 ASSERT(aurApp);
790 HandleEffect(aurApp, mode, apply);
791}
792
793void AuraEffect::ApplySpellMod(Unit* target, bool apply)
794{
795 if (!m_spellmod || target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
796 return;
797
798 target->ToPlayer()->AddSpellMod(m_spellmod, apply);
799
800 // Auras with charges do not mod amount of passive auras
801 if (GetBase()->IsUsingCharges())
802 return;
803 // reapply some passive spells after add/remove related spellmods
804 // Warning: it is a dead loop if 2 auras each other amount-shouldn't happen
805 switch (GetMiscValue())
806 {
807 case SPELLMOD_ALL_EFFECTS:
808 case SPELLMOD_EFFECT1:
809 case SPELLMOD_EFFECT2:
810 case SPELLMOD_EFFECT3:
811 {
812 ObjectGuid guid = target->GetGUID();
813 Unit::AuraApplicationMap& auras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
814 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::iterator iter = auras.begin(); iter != auras.end(); ++iter)
815 {
816 Aura* aura = iter->second->GetBase();
817 // only passive and permament auras-active auras should have amount set on spellcast and not be affected
818 // if aura is casted by others, it will not be affected
819 if ((aura->IsPassive() || aura->IsPermanent()) && aura->GetCasterGUID() == guid && aura->GetSpellInfo()->IsAffectedBySpellMod(m_spellmod))
820 {
821 if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_ALL_EFFECTS)
822 {
823 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
824 {
825 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(i))
826 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
827 }
828 }
829 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT1)
830 {
831 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(0))
832 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
833 }
834 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT2)
835 {
836 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(1))
837 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
838 }
839 else //if (modOp == SPELLMOD_EFFECT3)
840 {
841 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(2))
842 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
843 }
844 }
845 }
846
847 Pet* pet = target->ToPlayer()->GetPet();
848 if (!pet)
849 break;
850
851 ObjectGuid petguid = pet->GetGUID();
852 Unit::AuraApplicationMap& petauras = pet->GetAppliedAuras();
853 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::iterator iter = petauras.begin(); iter != petauras.end(); ++iter)
854 {
855 Aura* aura = iter->second->GetBase();
856 // only passive auras-active auras should have amount set on spellcast and not be affected
857 // if aura is casted by others, it will not be affected
858 if ((aura->IsPassive() || aura->IsPermanent()) && aura->GetCasterGUID() == petguid && aura->GetSpellInfo()->IsAffectedBySpellMod(m_spellmod))
859 {
860 if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_ALL_EFFECTS)
861 {
862 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
863 {
864 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(i))
865 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
866 }
867 }
868 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT1)
869 {
870 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(0))
871 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
872 }
873 else if (GetMiscValue() == SPELLMOD_EFFECT2)
874 {
875 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(1))
876 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
877 }
878 else //if (modOp == SPELLMOD_EFFECT3)
879 {
880 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = aura->GetEffect(2))
881 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
882 }
883 }
884 }
885 }
886 default:
887 break;
888 }
889}
890
891void AuraEffect::Update(uint32 diff, Unit* caster)
892{
893 if (m_isPeriodic && (GetBase()->GetDuration() >= 0 || GetBase()->IsPassive() || GetBase()->IsPermanent()))
894 {
895 uint32 totalTicks = GetTotalTicks();
896
897 m_periodicTimer -= int32(diff);
898 while (m_periodicTimer <= 0)
899 {
900 if (!GetBase()->IsPermanent() && (m_tickNumber + 1) > totalTicks)
901 {
902 break;
903 }
904
905 ++m_tickNumber;
906
907 // update before tick (aura can be removed in TriggerSpell or PeriodicTick calls)
908 m_periodicTimer += m_amplitude;
909 UpdatePeriodic(caster);
910
911 std::list<AuraApplication*> effectApplications;
912 GetApplicationList(effectApplications);
913 // tick on targets of effects
914 for (std::list<AuraApplication*>::const_iterator apptItr = effectApplications.begin(); apptItr != effectApplications.end(); ++apptItr)
915 if ((*apptItr)->HasEffect(GetEffIndex()))
916 PeriodicTick(*apptItr, caster);
917 }
918 }
919}
920
921void AuraEffect::UpdatePeriodic(Unit* caster)
922{
923 switch (GetAuraType())
924 {
925 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY:
926 switch (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName)
927 {
928 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
929 switch (GetId())
930 {
931 // Drink
932 case 430:
933 case 431:
934 case 432:
935 case 1133:
936 case 1135:
937 case 1137:
938 case 10250:
939 case 22734:
940 case 27089:
941 case 34291:
942 case 43182:
943 case 43183:
944 case 46755:
945 case 49472: // Drink Coffee
946 case 57073:
947 case 61830:
948 if (!caster || caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
949 return;
950 // Get SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN aura from spell
951 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = GetBase()->GetEffect(0))
952 {
953 if (aurEff->GetAuraType() != SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN)
954 {
955 m_isPeriodic = false;
956 LOG_ERROR("spells.aura.effect", "Aura {} structure has been changed - first aura is no longer SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN", GetId());
957 }
958 else
959 {
960 // default case - not in arena
961 if (!caster->ToPlayer()->InArena())
962 {
963 aurEff->ChangeAmount(GetAmount());
964 m_isPeriodic = false;
965 }
966 else
967 {
968 // **********************************************
969 // This feature uses only in arenas
970 // **********************************************
971 // Here need increase mana regen per tick (6 second rule)
972 // on 0 tick - 0 (handled in 2 second)
973 // on 1 tick - 166% (handled in 4 second)
974 // on 2 tick - 133% (handled in 6 second)
975
976 // Apply bonus for 1 - 4 tick
977 switch (m_tickNumber)
978 {
979 case 1: // 0%
980 aurEff->ChangeAmount(0);
981 break;
982 case 2: // 166%
983 aurEff->ChangeAmount(GetAmount() * 5 / 3);
984 break;
985 case 3: // 133%
986 aurEff->ChangeAmount(GetAmount() * 4 / 3);
987 break;
988 default: // 100% - normal regen
989 aurEff->ChangeAmount(GetAmount());
990 // No need to update after 4th tick
991 m_isPeriodic = false;
992 break;
993 }
994 }
995 }
996 }
997 break;
998 case 58549: // Tenacity
999 case 59911: // Tenacity (vehicle)
1000 GetBase()->RefreshDuration();
1001 break;
1002 case 66823:
1003 case 67618:
1004 case 67619:
1005 case 67620: // Paralytic Toxin
1006 // Get 0 effect aura
1007 if (AuraEffect* slow = GetBase()->GetEffect(0))
1008 {
1009 int32 newAmount = slow->GetAmount() - 10;
1010 if (newAmount < -100)
1011 newAmount = -100;
1012 slow->ChangeAmount(newAmount);
1013 }
1014 break;
1015 case 66020:
1016 // Get 0 effect aura
1017 if (AuraEffect* slow = GetBase()->GetEffect(0))
1018 {
1019 int32 newAmount = slow->GetAmount() + GetAmount();
1020 if (newAmount > 0)
1021 newAmount = 0;
1022 slow->ChangeAmount(newAmount);
1023 }
1024 break;
1025 default:
1026 break;
1027 }
1028 break;
1029 default:
1030 break;
1031 }
1032 default:
1033 break;
1034 }
1035 GetBase()->CallScriptEffectUpdatePeriodicHandlers(this);
1036}
1037
1038float AuraEffect::CalcPeriodicCritChance(Unit const* caster, Unit const* target) const
1039{
1040 float critChance = 0.0f;
1041 if (caster)
1042 {
1043 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
1044 {
1045 Unit::AuraEffectList const& mPeriodicCritAuras = modOwner->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_ABILITY_PERIODIC_CRIT);
1046 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator itr = mPeriodicCritAuras.begin(); itr != mPeriodicCritAuras.end(); ++itr)
1047 {
1048 if ((*itr)->IsAffectedOnSpell(GetSpellInfo()))
1049 {
1050 critChance = modOwner->SpellDoneCritChance(nullptr, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), (GetSpellInfo()->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED ? RANGED_ATTACK : BASE_ATTACK), true);
1051 break;
1052 }
1053 }
1054
1055 switch(GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName)
1056 {
1057 // Rupture - since 3.3.3 can crit
1058 case SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE:
1059 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x100000)
1060 critChance = modOwner->SpellDoneCritChance(nullptr, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), BASE_ATTACK, true);
1061 break;
1062 }
1063 }
1064 }
1065 if (target && critChance > 0.0f)
1066 critChance = target->SpellTakenCritChance(caster, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), critChance, BASE_ATTACK, true);
1067
1068 return std::max(0.0f, critChance);
1069}
1070
1071bool AuraEffect::IsAffectedOnSpell(SpellInfo const* spell) const
1072{
1073 if (!spell)
1074 return false;
1075 // Check family name
1076 if (spell->SpellFamilyName != m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
1077 return false;
1078
1079 // Check EffectClassMask
1080 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[m_effIndex].SpellClassMask & spell->SpellFamilyFlags)
1081 return true;
1082 return false;
1083}
1084
1085bool AuraEffect::HasSpellClassMask() const
1086{
1087 return m_spellInfo->Effects[m_effIndex].SpellClassMask;
1088}
1089
1090void AuraEffect::SendTickImmune(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
1091{
1092 if (caster)
1093 caster->SendSpellDamageImmune(target, m_spellInfo->Id);
1094}
1095
1096void AuraEffect::PeriodicTick(AuraApplication* aurApp, Unit* caster) const
1097{
1098 bool prevented = GetBase()->CallScriptEffectPeriodicHandlers(this, aurApp);
1099 if (prevented)
1100 return;
1101
1102 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1103
1104 switch (GetAuraType())
1105 {
1106 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY:
1107 HandlePeriodicDummyAuraTick(target, caster);
1108 break;
1109 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
1110 HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellAuraTick(target, caster);
1111 break;
1112 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_FROM_CLIENT:
1113 // Don't actually do anything - client will trigger casts of these spells by itself
1114 break;
1115 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
1116 HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellWithValueAuraTick(target, caster);
1117 break;
1118 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
1119 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
1120 HandlePeriodicDamageAurasTick(target, caster);
1121 break;
1122 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
1123 HandlePeriodicHealthLeechAuraTick(target, caster);
1124 break;
1125 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEALTH_FUNNEL:
1126 HandlePeriodicHealthFunnelAuraTick(target, caster);
1127 break;
1128 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
1129 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
1130 HandlePeriodicHealAurasTick(target, caster);
1131 break;
1132 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
1133 HandlePeriodicManaLeechAuraTick(target, caster);
1134 break;
1135 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
1136 HandleObsModPowerAuraTick(target, caster);
1137 break;
1138 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_ENERGIZE:
1139 HandlePeriodicEnergizeAuraTick(target, caster);
1140 break;
1141 case SPELL_AURA_POWER_BURN:
1142 HandlePeriodicPowerBurnAuraTick(target, caster);
1143 break;
1144 default:
1145 break;
1146 }
1147}
1148
1149void AuraEffect::HandleProc(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
1150{
1151 bool prevented = GetBase()->CallScriptEffectProcHandlers(this, aurApp, eventInfo);
1152 if (prevented)
1153 return;
1154
1155 switch (GetAuraType())
1156 {
1157 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
1158 HandleProcTriggerSpellAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1159 break;
1160 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
1161 HandleProcTriggerSpellWithValueAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1162 break;
1163 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_DAMAGE:
1164 HandleProcTriggerDamageAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1165 break;
1166 case SPELL_AURA_RAID_PROC_FROM_CHARGE:
1167 HandleRaidProcFromChargeAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1168 break;
1169 case SPELL_AURA_RAID_PROC_FROM_CHARGE_WITH_VALUE:
1170 HandleRaidProcFromChargeWithValueAuraProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1171 break;
1172 default:
1173 break;
1174 }
1175
1176 GetBase()->CallScriptAfterEffectProcHandlers(this, aurApp, eventInfo);
1177}
1178
1179void AuraEffect::CleanupTriggeredSpells(Unit* target)
1180{
1181 uint32 tSpellId = m_spellInfo->Effects[GetEffIndex()].TriggerSpell;
1182 if (!tSpellId)
1183 return;
1184
1185 SpellInfo const* tProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(tSpellId);
1186 if (!tProto)
1187 return;
1188
1189 if (tProto->GetDuration() != -1)
1190 return;
1191
1192 // needed for spell 43680, maybe others
1193 // TODO: is there a spell flag, which can solve this in a more sophisticated way?
1194 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[GetEffIndex()].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL &&
1195 uint32(m_spellInfo->GetDuration()) == m_spellInfo->Effects[GetEffIndex()].Amplitude)
1196 return;
1197
1198 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(tSpellId, GetCasterGUID());
1199}
1200
1201void AuraEffect::HandleShapeshiftBoosts(Unit* target, bool apply) const
1202{
1203 uint32 spellId = 0;
1204 uint32 spellId2 = 0;
1205 //uint32 spellId3 = 0;
1206 uint32 HotWSpellId = 0;
1207
1208 switch (GetMiscValue())
1209 {
1210 case FORM_CAT:
1211 spellId = 3025;
1212 HotWSpellId = 24900;
1213 break;
1214 case FORM_TREE:
1215 spellId = 34123;
1216 break;
1217 case FORM_TRAVEL:
1218 spellId = 5419;
1219 break;
1220 case FORM_AQUA:
1221 spellId = 5421;
1222 break;
1223 case FORM_BEAR:
1224 spellId = 1178;
1225 spellId2 = 21178;
1226 HotWSpellId = 24899;
1227 break;
1228 case FORM_DIREBEAR:
1229 spellId = 9635;
1230 spellId2 = 21178;
1231 HotWSpellId = 24899;
1232 break;
1233 case FORM_BATTLESTANCE:
1234 spellId = 21156;
1235 break;
1236 case FORM_DEFENSIVESTANCE:
1237 spellId = 7376;
1238 break;
1239 case FORM_BERSERKERSTANCE:
1240 spellId = 7381;
1241 break;
1242 case FORM_MOONKIN:
1243 spellId = 24905;
1244 spellId2 = 69366;
1245 break;
1246 case FORM_FLIGHT:
1247 spellId = 33948;
1248 spellId2 = 34764;
1249 break;
1250 case FORM_FLIGHT_EPIC:
1251 spellId = 40122;
1252 spellId2 = 40121;
1253 break;
1254 case FORM_METAMORPHOSIS:
1255 spellId = 54817;
1256 spellId2 = 54879;
1257 break;
1258 case FORM_SPIRITOFREDEMPTION:
1259 spellId = 27792;
1260 spellId2 = 27795; // must be second, this important at aura remove to prevent to early iterator invalidation.
1261 break;
1262 case FORM_SHADOW:
1263 spellId = 49868;
1264 spellId2 = 71167;
1265 break;
1266 case FORM_GHOSTWOLF:
1267 spellId = 67116;
1268 break;
1269 case FORM_GHOUL:
1270 case FORM_AMBIENT:
1271 case FORM_STEALTH:
1272 case FORM_CREATURECAT:
1273 case FORM_CREATUREBEAR:
1274 break;
1275 default:
1276 break;
1277 }
1278
1279 Player* player = target->ToPlayer();
1280 if (apply)
1281 {
1282 // Remove cooldown of spells triggered on stance change - they may share cooldown with stance spell
1283 if (spellId)
1284 {
1285 if (player)
1286 player->RemoveSpellCooldown(spellId);
1287 target->CastSpell(target, spellId, true, nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1288 }
1289
1290 if (spellId2)
1291 {
1292 if (player)
1293 player->RemoveSpellCooldown(spellId2);
1294 target->CastSpell(target, spellId2, true, nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1295 }
1296
1297 if (player)
1298 {
1299 const PlayerSpellMap& sp_list = player->GetSpellMap();
1300 for (PlayerSpellMap::const_iterator itr = sp_list.begin(); itr != sp_list.end(); ++itr)
1301 {
1302 if (itr->second->State == PLAYERSPELL_REMOVED || !itr->second->IsInSpec(player->GetActiveSpec()))
1303 continue;
1304
1305 if (itr->first == spellId || itr->first == spellId2)
1306 continue;
1307
1308 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(itr->first);
1309 if (!spellInfo || !spellInfo->HasAttribute(SpellAttr0(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE | SPELL_ATTR0_DO_NOT_DISPLAY)))
1310 continue;
1311
1312 if (spellInfo->Stances & (1 << (GetMiscValue() - 1)))
1313 target->CastSpell(target, itr->first, true, nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1314 }
1315
1316 // xinef: talent stance auras are not on m_spells map, so iterate talents
1317 const PlayerTalentMap& tl_list = player->GetTalentMap();
1318 for (PlayerTalentMap::const_iterator itr = tl_list.begin(); itr != tl_list.end(); ++itr)
1319 {
1320 if (itr->second->State == PLAYERSPELL_REMOVED || !itr->second->IsInSpec(player->GetActiveSpec()))
1321 continue;
1322
1323 if (itr->first == spellId || itr->first == spellId2)
1324 continue;
1325
1326 // Xinef: skip talents with effect learn spell
1327 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(itr->first);
1328 if (!spellInfo || !spellInfo->HasAttribute(SpellAttr0(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE | SPELL_ATTR0_DO_NOT_DISPLAY)) || spellInfo->HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL))
1329 continue;
1330
1331 if (spellInfo->Stances & (1 << (GetMiscValue() - 1)))
1332 target->CastSpell(target, itr->first, true, nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1333 }
1334
1335 // Also do it for Glyphs
1336 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_GLYPH_SLOT_INDEX; ++i)
1337 {
1338 if (uint32 glyphId = player->GetGlyph(i))
1339 {
1340 if (GlyphPropertiesEntry const* glyph = sGlyphPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(glyphId))
1341 {
1342 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(glyph->SpellId);
1343 if (!spellInfo || !spellInfo->HasAttribute(SpellAttr0(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE | SPELL_ATTR0_DO_NOT_DISPLAY)))
1344 continue;
1345 if (spellInfo->Stances & (1 << (GetMiscValue() - 1)))
1346 target->CastSpell(target, glyph->SpellId, TriggerCastFlags(TRIGGERED_FULL_MASK & ~(TRIGGERED_IGNORE_SHAPESHIFT | TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_AURASTATE)), nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1347 }
1348 }
1349 }
1350
1351 // Leader of the Pack
1352 if (player->HasTalent(17007, player->GetActiveSpec()))
1353 {
1354 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(24932);
1355 if (spellInfo && spellInfo->Stances & (1 << (GetMiscValue() - 1)))
1356 target->CastSpell(target, 24932, true, nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1357 }
1358 // Improved Barkskin - apply/remove armor bonus due to shapeshift
1359 if (player->HasTalent(63410, player->GetActiveSpec()) || player->HasTalent(63411, player->GetActiveSpec()))
1360 {
1361 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(66530);
1362 if (GetMiscValue() == FORM_TRAVEL || GetMiscValue() == FORM_NONE) // "while in Travel Form or while not shapeshifted"
1363 target->CastSpell(target, 66530, true);
1364 }
1365 // Heart of the Wild
1366 if (HotWSpellId)
1367 {
1368 // hacky, but the only way as spell family is not SPELLFAMILY_DRUID
1369 Unit::AuraEffectList const& mModTotalStatPct = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_TOTAL_STAT_PERCENTAGE);
1370 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = mModTotalStatPct.begin(); i != mModTotalStatPct.end(); ++i)
1371 {
1372 // Heart of the Wild
1373 if ((*i)->GetSpellInfo()->SpellIconID == 240 && (*i)->GetMiscValue() == STAT_INTELLECT)
1374 {
1375 int32 HotWMod = (*i)->GetAmount() / 2; // For each 2% Intelligence, you get 1% stamina and 1% attack power.
1376
1377 target->CastCustomSpell(target, HotWSpellId, &HotWMod, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1378 break;
1379 }
1380 }
1381 }
1382 switch (GetMiscValue())
1383 {
1384 case FORM_CAT:
1385 // Savage Roar
1386 if (target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_DUMMY, SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, 0, 0x10000000, 0))
1387 target->CastSpell(target, 62071, true);
1388 // Nurturing Instinct
1389 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_HEALING_OF_STAT_PERCENT, SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, 2254, 0))
1390 {
1391 uint32 spellId3 = 0;
1392 switch (aurEff->GetId())
1393 {
1394 case 33872:
1395 spellId3 = 47179;
1396 break;
1397 case 33873:
1398 spellId3 = 47180;
1399 break;
1400 }
1401 target->CastSpell(target, spellId3, true, nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1402 }
1403 // Master Shapeshifter - Cat
1404 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetDummyAuraEffect(SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC, 2851, 0))
1405 {
1406 int32 bp = aurEff->GetAmount();
1407 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 48420, &bp, nullptr, nullptr, true);
1408 }
1409 break;
1410 case FORM_DIREBEAR:
1411 case FORM_BEAR:
1412 // Master Shapeshifter - Bear
1413 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetDummyAuraEffect(SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC, 2851, 0))
1414 {
1415 int32 bp = aurEff->GetAmount();
1416 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 48418, &bp, nullptr, nullptr, true);
1417 }
1418 // Survival of the Fittest
1419 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_TOTAL_STAT_PERCENTAGE, SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, 961, 0))
1420 {
1421 int32 bp = aurEff->GetSpellInfo()->Effects[EFFECT_2].CalcValue();
1422 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 62069, &bp, nullptr, nullptr, true, 0, this, target->GetGUID());
1423 }
1424 break;
1425 case FORM_MOONKIN:
1426 // Master Shapeshifter - Moonkin
1427 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetDummyAuraEffect(SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC, 2851, 0))
1428 {
1429 int32 bp = aurEff->GetAmount();
1430 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 48421, &bp, nullptr, nullptr, true);
1431 }
1432 // Always cast Moonkin Aura
1433 target->CastSpell(target, 24907, true, nullptr, this, target->GetGUID());
1434 break;
1435 // Master Shapeshifter - Tree of Life
1436 case FORM_TREE:
1437 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->GetDummyAuraEffect(SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC, 2851, 0))
1438 {
1439 int32 bp = aurEff->GetAmount();
1440 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 48422, &bp, nullptr, nullptr, true);
1441 }
1442 break;
1443 }
1444 }
1445 }
1446 else
1447 {
1448 if (spellId)
1449 target->RemoveOwnedAura(spellId);
1450 if (spellId2)
1451 target->RemoveOwnedAura(spellId2);
1452
1453 // Improved Barkskin - apply/remove armor bonus due to shapeshift
1454 if (player)
1455 {
1456 if (player->HasTalent(63410, player->GetActiveSpec()) || player->HasTalent(63411, player->GetActiveSpec()))
1457 {
1458 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(66530);
1459 target->CastSpell(target, 66530, true);
1460 }
1461 }
1462
1463 const Unit::AuraEffectList& shapeshifts = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT);
1464 AuraEffect* newAura = nullptr;
1465 // Iterate through all the shapeshift auras that the target has, if there is another aura with SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT, then this aura is being removed due to that one being applied
1466 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator itr = shapeshifts.begin(); itr != shapeshifts.end(); ++itr)
1467 {
1468 if ((*itr) != this)
1469 {
1470 newAura = *itr;
1471 break;
1472 }
1473 }
1474
1475 // Use the new aura to see on what stance the target will be
1476 uint32 newStance = (1 << ((newAura ? newAura->GetMiscValue() : 0) - 1));
1477
1478 Unit::AuraApplicationMap& tAuras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
1479 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::iterator itr = tAuras.begin(); itr != tAuras.end();)
1480 {
1481 // If the stances are not compatible with the spell, remove it
1482 // Xinef: Remove all passive auras, they will be added if needed
1483 if (itr->second->GetBase()->IsRemovedOnShapeLost(target) && (!(itr->second->GetBase()->GetSpellInfo()->Stances & newStance) || itr->second->GetBase()->IsPassive()))
1484 target->RemoveAura(itr);
1485 else
1486 ++itr;
1487 }
1488
1489 // Xinef: Remove autoattack spells
1490 if (Spell* spell = target->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_MELEE_SPELL))
1491 if (spell->GetSpellInfo()->CheckShapeshift(newAura ? newAura->GetMiscValue() : 0) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
1492 spell->cancel(true);
1493 }
1494}
1495
1496/*********************************************************/
1497/*** AURA EFFECT HANDLERS ***/
1498/*********************************************************/

1500/**************************************/
1501/*** VISIBILITY & PHASES ***/
1502/**************************************/
1503
1504void AuraEffect::HandleModInvisibilityDetect(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1505{
1506 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
1507 return;
1508
1509 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1510 InvisibilityType type = InvisibilityType(GetMiscValue());
1511
1512 if (apply)
1513 {
1514 target->m_invisibilityDetect.AddFlag(type);
1515 target->m_invisibilityDetect.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1516 }
1517 else
1518 {
1519 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INVISIBILITY_DETECT))
1520 target->m_invisibilityDetect.DelFlag(type);
1521
1522 target->m_invisibilityDetect.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1523 }
1524
1525 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1526 target->UpdateObjectVisibility(target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER || target->GetOwnerGUID().IsPlayer());
1527}
1528
1529void AuraEffect::HandleModInvisibility(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1530{
1531 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
1532 return;
1533
1534 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1535 InvisibilityType type = InvisibilityType(GetMiscValue());
1536
1537 if (apply)
1538 {
1539 // apply glow vision
1540 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (type == INVISIBILITY_GENERAL || type == INVISIBILITY_UNK10))
1541 target->SetByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES_2_OFFSET_AURA_VISION, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_INVISIBILITY_GLOW);
1542
1543 target->m_invisibility.AddFlag(type);
1544 target->m_invisibility.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1545 }
1546 else
1547 {
1548 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INVISIBILITY))
1549 {
1550 // if not have different invisibility auras.
1551 // always remove glow vision
1552 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1553 target->RemoveByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, 3, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_INVISIBILITY_GLOW);
1554
1555 target->m_invisibility.DelFlag(type);
1556 }
1557 else
1558 {
1559 bool found = false;
1560 Unit::AuraEffectList const& invisAuras = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INVISIBILITY);
1561 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = invisAuras.begin(); i != invisAuras.end(); ++i)
1562 {
1563 if (GetMiscValue() == (*i)->GetMiscValue())
1564 {
1565 found = true;
1566 break;
1567 }
1568 }
1569 if (!found)
1570 {
1571 target->m_invisibility.DelFlag(type);
1572
1573 // if not have invisibility auras of type INVISIBILITY_GENERAL
1574 // remove glow vision
1575 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !target->m_invisibility.HasFlag(INVISIBILITY_GENERAL) && !target->m_invisibility.HasFlag(INVISIBILITY_UNK10))
1576 {
1577 target->RemoveByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES_2_OFFSET_AURA_VISION, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_INVISIBILITY_GLOW);
1578 }
1579 }
1580 }
1581
1582 target->m_invisibility.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1583 }
1584
1585 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1586 if (apply && (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1587 {
1588 // drop flag at invisibiliy in bg
1589 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
1590 }
1591
1592 target->UpdateObjectVisibility(target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER || target->GetOwnerGUID().IsPlayer() || target->GetMap()->Instanceable(), true);
1593 target->bRequestForcedVisibilityUpdate = false;
1594}
1595
1596void AuraEffect::HandleModStealthDetect(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1597{
1598 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
1599 return;
1600
1601 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1602 StealthType type = StealthType(GetMiscValue());
1603
1604 if (apply)
1605 {
1606 target->m_stealthDetect.AddFlag(type);
1607 target->m_stealthDetect.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1608 }
1609 else
1610 {
1611 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH_DETECT))
1612 target->m_stealthDetect.DelFlag(type);
1613
1614 target->m_stealthDetect.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1615 }
1616
1617 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1618 target->UpdateObjectVisibility(target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER || target->GetOwnerGUID().IsPlayer());
1619}
1620
1621void AuraEffect::HandleModStealth(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1622{
1623 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
1624 return;
1625
1626 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1627 StealthType type = StealthType(GetMiscValue());
1628
1629 if (apply)
1630 {
1631 target->m_stealth.AddFlag(type);
1632 target->m_stealth.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1633
1634 target->SetStandFlags(UNIT_STAND_FLAGS_CREEP);
1635 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1636 target->SetByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, 3, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_STEALTH);
1637
1638 // interrupt autoshot
1639 if (target->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL))
1640 {
1641 target->FinishSpell(CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL);
1642 target->ToPlayer()->SendAutoRepeatCancel(target);
1643 }
1644 }
1645 else
1646 {
1647 target->m_stealth.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1648
1649 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH)) // if last SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH
1650 {
1651 target->m_stealth.DelFlag(type);
1652
1653 target->RemoveStandFlags(UNIT_STAND_FLAGS_CREEP);
1654 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1655 target->RemoveByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, 3, PLAYER_FIELD_BYTE2_STEALTH);
1656 }
1657 }
1658
1659 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1660 if (apply && (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1661 {
1662 // drop flag at stealth in bg
1663 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
1664 }
1665
1666 target->UpdateObjectVisibility(target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER || target->GetOwnerGUID().IsPlayer() || target->GetMap()->Instanceable(), true);
1667 target->bRequestForcedVisibilityUpdate = false;
1668}
1669
1670void AuraEffect::HandleModStealthLevel(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1671{
1672 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
1673 return;
1674
1675 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1676 StealthType type = StealthType(GetMiscValue());
1677
1678 if (apply)
1679 target->m_stealth.AddValue(type, GetAmount());
1680 else
1681 target->m_stealth.AddValue(type, -GetAmount());
1682
1683 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1684 target->UpdateObjectVisibility(target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER || target->GetOwnerGUID().IsPlayer());
1685}
1686
1687void AuraEffect::HandleDetectAmore(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1688{
1689 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
1690 {
1691 return;
1692 }
1693
1694 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1695 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
1696 {
1697 return;
1698 }
1699
1700 if (apply)
1701 {
1702 target->SetByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, 3, 1 << (GetMiscValue() - 1));
1703 }
1704 else
1705 {
1706 if (target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_DETECT_AMORE))
1707 {
1708 Unit::AuraEffectList const& amoreAuras = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_DETECT_AMORE);
1709 for (AuraEffect const* aurEff : amoreAuras)
1710 if (GetMiscValue() == aurEff->GetMiscValue())
1711 {
1712 return;
1713 }
1714 }
1715
1716 target->RemoveByteFlag(PLAYER_FIELD_BYTES2, 3, 1 << (GetMiscValue() - 1));
1717 }
1718}
1719
1720void AuraEffect::HandleSpiritOfRedemption(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1721{
1722 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1723 return;
1724
1725 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1726
1727 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
1728 return;
1729
1730 // prepare spirit state
1731 if (apply)
1732 {
1733 // disable breath/etc timers
1734 target->ToPlayer()->StopMirrorTimers();
1735
1736 // set stand state (expected in this form)
1737 if (!target->IsStandState())
1738 target->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND);
1739
1740 target->SetHealth(1);
1741 }
1742 // die at aura end
1743 else if (target->IsAlive())
1744 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1745 target->setDeathState(JUST_DIED);
1746
1747 // xinef: damage immunity spell, not needed because of 93 aura (adds non_attackable state)
1748 // xinef: probably blizzard added it just in case in wotlk (id > 46000)
1749 if (apply)
1750 target->CastSpell(target, 62371, true);
1751 else
1752 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(62371);
1753}
1754
1755void AuraEffect::HandleAuraGhost(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1756{
1757 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
1758 return;
1759
1760 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1761
1762 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
1763 return;
1764
1765 if (apply)
1766 {
1767 target->ToPlayer()->SetPlayerFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS_GHOST);
1768 target->m_serverSideVisibility.SetValue(SERVERSIDE_VISIBILITY_GHOST, GHOST_VISIBILITY_GHOST);
1769 target->m_serverSideVisibilityDetect.SetValue(SERVERSIDE_VISIBILITY_GHOST, GHOST_VISIBILITY_GHOST);
1770 }
1771 else
1772 {
1773 if (target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_GHOST))
1774 return;
1775
1776 target->ToPlayer()->RemovePlayerFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS_GHOST);
1777 target->m_serverSideVisibility.SetValue(SERVERSIDE_VISIBILITY_GHOST, GHOST_VISIBILITY_ALIVE);
1778 target->m_serverSideVisibilityDetect.SetValue(SERVERSIDE_VISIBILITY_GHOST, GHOST_VISIBILITY_ALIVE);
1779 }
1780}
1781
1782void AuraEffect::HandlePhase(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1783{
1784 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
1785 return;
1786
1787 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1788
1789 // no-phase is also phase state so same code for apply and remove
1790 uint32 newPhase = target->GetPhaseByAuras();
1791
1792 if (Player* player = target->ToPlayer())
1793 {
1794 if (!newPhase)
1795 newPhase = PHASEMASK_NORMAL;
1796
1797 // do not change phase to GM with all phases enabled
1798 if (player->IsGameMaster())
1799 newPhase = PHASEMASK_ANYWHERE;
1800
1801 player->SetPhaseMask(newPhase, false);
1802 player->GetSession()->SendSetPhaseShift(newPhase);
1803 }
1804 else
1805 {
1806 if (!newPhase)
1807 {
1808 newPhase = PHASEMASK_NORMAL;
1809 if (Creature* creature = target->ToCreature())
1810 if (CreatureData const* data = sObjectMgr->GetCreatureData(creature->GetSpawnId()))
1811 newPhase = data->phaseMask;
1812 }
1813
1814 target->SetPhaseMask(newPhase, false);
1815 }
1816
1817 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
1818 // phase auras normally not expected at BG but anyway better check
1819 if (apply)
1820 {
1821 // drop flag at invisibiliy in bg
1822 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
1823 }
1824
1825 // need triggering visibility update base at phase update of not GM invisible (other GMs anyway see in any phases)
1826 if (target->IsVisible())
1827 {
1828 if (!target->GetMap()->Instanceable())
1829 {
1830 target->UpdateObjectVisibility(false);
1831 target->m_last_notify_position.Relocate(-5000.0f, -5000.0f, -5000.0f);
1832 }
1833 else
1834 target->UpdateObjectVisibility();
1835 }
1836}
1837
1838/**********************/
1839/*** UNIT MODEL ***/
1840/**********************/
1841
1842void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModShapeshift(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
1843{
1844 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL_OR_REAPPLY_MASK))
1845 return;
1846
1847 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1848
1849 uint32 modelid = 0;
1850 Powers PowerType = POWER_MANA;
1851 ShapeshiftForm form = ShapeshiftForm(GetMiscValue());
1852
1853 switch (form)
1854 {
1855 case FORM_CAT: // 0x01
1856 case FORM_GHOUL: // 0x07
1857 PowerType = POWER_ENERGY;
1858 break;
1859
1860 case FORM_BEAR: // 0x05
1861 case FORM_DIREBEAR: // 0x08
1862
1863 case FORM_BATTLESTANCE: // 0x11
1864 case FORM_DEFENSIVESTANCE: // 0x12
1865 case FORM_BERSERKERSTANCE: // 0x13
1866 PowerType = POWER_RAGE;
1867 break;
1868
1869 case FORM_TREE: // 0x02
1870 case FORM_TRAVEL: // 0x03
1871 case FORM_AQUA: // 0x04
1872 case FORM_AMBIENT: // 0x06
1873
1874 case FORM_STEVES_GHOUL: // 0x09
1875 case FORM_THARONJA_SKELETON: // 0x0A
1876 case FORM_TEST_OF_STRENGTH: // 0x0B
1877 case FORM_BLB_PLAYER: // 0x0C
1878 case FORM_SHADOW_DANCE: // 0x0D
1879 case FORM_CREATUREBEAR: // 0x0E
1880 case FORM_CREATURECAT: // 0x0F
1881 case FORM_GHOSTWOLF: // 0x10
1882
1883 case FORM_TEST: // 0x14
1884 case FORM_ZOMBIE: // 0x15
1885 case FORM_METAMORPHOSIS: // 0x16
1886 case FORM_UNDEAD: // 0x19
1887 case FORM_MASTER_ANGLER: // 0x1A
1888 case FORM_FLIGHT_EPIC: // 0x1B
1889 case FORM_SHADOW: // 0x1C
1890 case FORM_FLIGHT: // 0x1D
1891 case FORM_STEALTH: // 0x1E
1892 case FORM_MOONKIN: // 0x1F
1893 case FORM_SPIRITOFREDEMPTION: // 0x20
1894 break;
1895 default:
1896 LOG_ERROR("spells.aura.effect", "Auras: Unknown Shapeshift Type: {}", GetMiscValue());
1897 }
1898
1899 modelid = target->GetModelForForm(form);
1900
1901 if (apply)
1902 {
1903 // remove polymorph before changing display id to keep new display id
1904 switch (form)
1905 {
1906 case FORM_CAT:
1907 case FORM_TREE:
1908 case FORM_TRAVEL:
1909 case FORM_AQUA:
1910 case FORM_BEAR:
1911 case FORM_DIREBEAR:
1912 case FORM_FLIGHT_EPIC:
1913 case FORM_FLIGHT:
1914 case FORM_MOONKIN:
1915 {
1916 if (Player* player = target->ToPlayer())
1917 {
1918 player->SetCanTeleport(true);
1919 }
1920 // remove movement affects
1921 target->RemoveAurasByShapeShift();
1922
1923 // and polymorphic affects
1924 if (target->IsPolymorphed())
1925 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(target->getTransForm());
1926 break;
1927 }
1928 default:
1929 break;
1930 }
1931
1932 // remove other shapeshift before applying a new one
1933 // xinef: rogue shouldnt be wrapped by this check (shadow dance vs stealth)
1934 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName != SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE)
1935 target->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT, ObjectGuid::Empty, GetBase());
1936
1937 // stop handling the effect if it was removed by linked event
1938 if (aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
1939 return;
1940
1941 if (PowerType != POWER_MANA)
1942 {
1943 uint32 oldPower = target->GetPower(PowerType);
1944 // reset power to default values only at power change
1945 if (target->getPowerType() != PowerType)
1946 target->setPowerType(PowerType);
1947
1948 switch (form)
1949 {
1950 case FORM_CAT:
1951 case FORM_BEAR:
1952 case FORM_DIREBEAR:
1953 {
1954 // get furor proc chance
1955 uint32 FurorChance = 0;
1956 if (AuraEffect const* dummy = target->GetDummyAuraEffect(SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, 238, 0))
1957 FurorChance = std::max(dummy->GetAmount(), 0);
1958
1959 switch (GetMiscValue())
1960 {
1961 case FORM_CAT:
1962 {
1963 int32 basePoints = int32(std::min(oldPower, FurorChance));
1964 target->SetPower(POWER_ENERGY, 0);
1965 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 17099, &basePoints, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, this);
1966 break;
1967 }
1968 case FORM_BEAR:
1969 case FORM_DIREBEAR:
1970 if (urand(0, 99) < FurorChance)
1971 target->CastSpell(target, 17057, true);
1972 break;
1973 default:
1974 {
1975 uint32 newEnergy = std::min(target->GetPower(POWER_ENERGY), FurorChance);
1976 target->SetPower(POWER_ENERGY, newEnergy);
1977 break;
1978 }
1979 }
1980 break;
1981 }
1982 default:
1983 break;
1984 }
1985 }
1986 // stop handling the effect if it was removed by linked event
1987 if (aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
1988 return;
1989
1990 target->SetShapeshiftForm(form);
1991 // xinef: allow shapeshift to override model id if forced transform aura is not present!
1992 if (modelid > 0)
1993 {
1994 bool allow = true;
1995 if (target->getTransForm())
1996 if (SpellInfo const* transformSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(target->getTransForm()))
1997 if (transformSpellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NO_IMMUNITIES) || !transformSpellInfo->IsPositive())
1998 allow = false;
1999
2000 if (allow)
2001 target->SetDisplayId(modelid);
2002 }
2003 }
2004 else
2005 {
2006 // reset model id if no other auras present
2007 // may happen when aura is applied on linked event on aura removal
2008 if (!target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT))
2009 {
2010 target->SetShapeshiftForm(FORM_NONE);
2011 if (target->getClass() == CLASS_DRUID)
2012 {
2013 target->setPowerType(POWER_MANA);
2014 // Remove movement impairing effects also when shifting out
2015 target->RemoveAurasByShapeShift();
2016 }
2017 }
2018
2019 if (modelid > 0)
2020 target->RestoreDisplayId();
2021
2022 switch (form)
2023 {
2024 // Nordrassil Harness - bonus
2025 case FORM_BEAR:
2026 case FORM_DIREBEAR:
2027 case FORM_CAT:
2028 if (AuraEffect* dummy = target->GetAuraEffect(37315, 0))
2029 target->CastSpell(target, 37316, true, nullptr, dummy);
2030 break;
2031 // Nordrassil Regalia - bonus
2032 case FORM_MOONKIN:
2033 if (AuraEffect* dummy = target->GetAuraEffect(37324, 0))
2034 target->CastSpell(target, 37325, true, nullptr, dummy);
2035 break;
2036 case FORM_BATTLESTANCE:
2037 case FORM_DEFENSIVESTANCE:
2038 case FORM_BERSERKERSTANCE:
2039 {
2040 uint32 Rage_val = 0;
2041 // Defensive Tactics
2042 if (form == FORM_DEFENSIVESTANCE)
2043 {
2044 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = target->IsScriptOverriden(m_spellInfo, 831))
2045 Rage_val += aurEff->GetAmount() * 10;
2046 }
2047 // Stance mastery + Tactical mastery (both passive, and last have aura only in defense stance, but need apply at any stance switch)
2048 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2049 {
2050 // Stance mastery - trainer spell
2051 PlayerSpellMap const& sp_list = target->ToPlayer()->GetSpellMap();
2052 for (PlayerSpellMap::const_iterator itr = sp_list.begin(); itr != sp_list.end(); ++itr)
2053 {
2054 if (itr->second->State == PLAYERSPELL_REMOVED || !itr->second->IsInSpec(target->ToPlayer()->GetActiveSpec()))
2055 continue;
2056
2057 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(itr->first);
2058 if (spellInfo && spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR && spellInfo->SpellIconID == 139)
2059 Rage_val += target->CalculateSpellDamage(target, spellInfo, 0) * 10;
2060 }
2061
2062 // Tactical Mastery - talent
2063 PlayerTalentMap const& tp_list = target->ToPlayer()->GetTalentMap();
2064 for (PlayerTalentMap::const_iterator itr = tp_list.begin(); itr != tp_list.end(); ++itr)
2065 {
2066 if (itr->second->State == PLAYERSPELL_REMOVED || !itr->second->IsInSpec(target->ToPlayer()->GetActiveSpec()))
2067 continue;
2068
2069 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(itr->first);
2070 if (spellInfo && spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR && spellInfo->SpellIconID == 139)
2071 Rage_val += target->CalculateSpellDamage(target, spellInfo, 0) * 10;
2072 }
2073 }
2074 if (target->GetPower(POWER_RAGE) > Rage_val)
2075 target->SetPower(POWER_RAGE, Rage_val);
2076 break;
2077 }
2078 default:
2079 break;
2080 }
2081 }
2082
2083 // adding/removing linked auras
2084 // add/remove the shapeshift aura's boosts
2085 HandleShapeshiftBoosts(target, apply);
2086
2087 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2088 target->ToPlayer()->InitDataForForm();
2089
2090 if (target->getClass() == CLASS_DRUID)
2091 {
2092 // Dash
2093 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_SPEED, SPELLFAMILY_DRUID, 0, 0, 0x8))
2094 aurEff->RecalculateAmount();
2095
2096 // Disarm handling
2097 // If druid shifts while being disarmed we need to deal with that since forms aren't affected by disarm
2098 // and also HandleAuraModDisarm is not triggered
2099 if (!target->CanUseAttackType(BASE_ATTACK))
2100 {
2101 if (Item* pItem = target->ToPlayer()->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND))
2102 {
2103 target->ToPlayer()->_ApplyWeaponDamage(EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND, pItem->GetTemplate(), nullptr, apply);
2104 }
2105 }
2106 }
2107
2108 // stop handling the effect if it was removed by linked event
2109 if (apply && aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
2110 return;
2111
2112 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2113 {
2114 SpellShapeshiftEntry const* shapeInfo = sSpellShapeshiftStore.LookupEntry(form);
2115 // Learn spells for shapeshift form - no need to send action bars or add spells to spellbook
2116 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SHAPESHIFT_SPELLS; ++i)
2117 {
2118 if (!shapeInfo->stanceSpell[i])
2119 continue;
2120 if (apply)
2121 target->ToPlayer()->_addSpell(shapeInfo->stanceSpell[i], SPEC_MASK_ALL, true);
2122 else
2123 target->ToPlayer()->removeSpell(shapeInfo->stanceSpell[i], SPEC_MASK_ALL, true);
2124 }
2125 }
2126}

2199 case 42365:

2269 break;
2270 // Gnomeregan Pride
2271 case 75531:
2272 target->SetDisplayId(target->getGender() == GENDER_MALE ? 31654 : 31655);
2273 break;
2274 default:
2275 break;
2276 }
2277 }
2278 else
2279 {
2280 CreatureTemplate const* ci = sObjectMgr->GetCreatureTemplate(GetMiscValue());
2281 if (!ci)
2282 {
2283 target->SetDisplayId(16358); // pig pink ^_^
2284 LOG_ERROR("spells.aura.effect", "Auras: unknown creature id = {} (only need its modelid) From Spell Aura Transform in Spell ID = {}", GetMiscValue(), GetId());
2285 }
2286 else
2287 {
2288 uint32 model_id = 0;
2289
2290 if (uint32 modelid = ci->GetRandomValidModelId())
2291 model_id = modelid; // Will use the default model here
2292
2293 // Polymorph (sheep)
2294 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_MAGE && GetSpellInfo()->SpellIconID == 82 && GetSpellInfo()->SpellVisual[0] == 12978)
2295 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
2296 if (caster->HasAura(52648)) // Glyph of the Penguin
2297 model_id = 26452;
2298
2299 target->SetDisplayId(model_id);
2300
2301 // Dragonmaw Illusion (set mount model also)
2302 if (GetId() == 42016 && target->GetMountID() && !target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED).empty())
2303 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_MOUNTDISPLAYID, 16314);
2304 }
2305 }
2306 }
2307
2308 // update active transform spell only when transform or shapeshift not set or not overwriting negative by positive case
2309 SpellInfo const* transformSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(target->getTransForm());
2310 if (!transformSpellInfo || GetSpellInfo()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NO_IMMUNITIES) || !GetSpellInfo()->IsPositive() || transformSpellInfo->IsPositive())
2311 target->setTransForm(GetId());
2312
2313 // polymorph case
2314 if ((mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL) && target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && target->IsPolymorphed())
2315 {
2316 // for players, start regeneration after 1s (in polymorph fast regeneration case)
2317 // only if caster is Player (after patch 2.4.2)
2318 if (GetCasterGUID().IsPlayer())
2319 target->ToPlayer()->setRegenTimerCount(1 * IN_MILLISECONDS);
2320
2321 //dismount polymorphed target (after patch 2.4.2)
2322 if (target->IsMounted())
2323 target->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED);
2324 }
2325 }
2326 else
2327 {
2328 // HandleEffect(this, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT, true) will reapply it if need
2329 if (target->getTransForm() == GetId())
2330 target->setTransForm(0);
2331
2332 target->RestoreDisplayId();
2333
2334 // Dragonmaw Illusion (restore mount model)
2335 if (GetId() == 42016 && target->GetMountID() == 16314)
2336 {
2337 if (!target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED).empty())
2338 {
2339 uint32 cr_id = target->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED).front()->GetMiscValue();
2340 if (CreatureTemplate const* ci = sObjectMgr->GetCreatureTemplate(cr_id))
2341 {
2342 uint32 displayID = ObjectMgr::ChooseDisplayId(ci);
2343 sObjectMgr->GetCreatureModelRandomGender(&displayID);
2344
2345 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_MOUNTDISPLAYID, displayID);
2346 }
2347 }
2348 }
2349 }
2350}

2352void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModScale(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2353{
2354 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2355 return;
2356
2357 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2358
2359 float scale = target->GetObjectScale();
2360 ApplyPercentModFloatVar(scale, float(GetAmount()), apply);
2361 target->SetObjectScale(scale);
2362}
2363
2364void AuraEffect::HandleAuraCloneCaster(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2365{
2366 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2367 return;
2368
2369 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2370
2371 if (apply)
2372 {
2373 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2374 if (!caster || caster == target)
2375 return;
2376
2377 // What must be cloned? at least display and scale
2378 target->SetDisplayId(caster->GetDisplayId());
2379 target->SetUnitFlag2(UNIT_FLAG2_MIRROR_IMAGE);
2380 }
2381 else
2382 {
2383 target->SetDisplayId(target->GetNativeDisplayId());
2384 target->RemoveUnitFlag2(UNIT_FLAG2_MIRROR_IMAGE);
2385 }
2386}

2389/*** FIGHT ***/
2390/************************/
2391
2392void AuraEffect::HandleFeignDeath(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2393{
2394 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2395 return;
2396
2397 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2398
2399 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
2400 return;
2401
2402 if (Player* targetPlayer = target->ToPlayer())
2403 {
2404 sScriptMgr->AnticheatSetUnderACKmount(targetPlayer);
2405 }
2406
2407 if (apply)
2408 {
2409 /*
2410 WorldPacket data(SMSG_FEIGN_DEATH_RESISTED, 9);
2411 data<<target->GetGUID();
2412 data<<uint8(0);
2413 target->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
2414 */
2415
2416 UnitList targets;
2417 Acore::AnyUnfriendlyUnitInObjectRangeCheck u_check(target, target, target->GetVisibilityRange()); // no VISIBILITY_COMPENSATION, distance is enough
2418 Acore::UnitListSearcher<Acore::AnyUnfriendlyUnitInObjectRangeCheck> searcher(target, targets, u_check);
2419 Cell::VisitAllObjects(target, searcher, target->GetMap()->GetVisibilityRange());
2420 for (UnitList::iterator iter = targets.begin(); iter != targets.end(); ++iter)
2421 {
2422 if (!(*iter)->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING))
2423 continue;
2424
2425 for (uint32 i = CURRENT_FIRST_NON_MELEE_SPELL; i < CURRENT_MAX_SPELL; i++)
2426 {
2427 if ((*iter)->GetCurrentSpell(i) && (*iter)->GetCurrentSpell(i)->m_targets.GetUnitTargetGUID() == target->GetGUID())
2428 {
2429 SpellInfo const* si = (*iter)->GetCurrentSpell(i)->GetSpellInfo();
2430 if (si->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_IGNORE_PHASE_SHIFT) && (*iter)->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
2431 {
2432 Creature* c = (*iter)->ToCreature();
2433 if ((!c->IsPet() && c->GetCreatureTemplate()->rank == CREATURE_ELITE_WORLDBOSS) || c->isWorldBoss() || c->IsDungeonBoss())
2434 continue;
2435 }
2436 bool interrupt = false; // pussywizard: skip spells that don't target units, but casted on unit (eg. TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY)
2437 for (uint8 j = 0; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
2438 if (si->Effects[j].Effect && (si->Effects[j].GetUsedTargetObjectType() == TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT || si->Effects[j].GetUsedTargetObjectType() == TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST))
2439 {
2440 // at least one effect truly targets an unit, interrupt the spell
2441 interrupt = true;
2442 break;
2443 }
2444 if (interrupt)
2445 (*iter)->InterruptSpell(CurrentSpellTypes(i), false);
2446 }
2447 }
2448 }
2449
2450 if (target->GetInstanceScript() && target->GetInstanceScript()->IsEncounterInProgress())
2451 {
2452 // Xinef: replaced with CombatStop(false)
2453 target->AttackStop();
2454 target->RemoveAllAttackers();
2455 target->getHostileRefMgr().addThreatPercent(-100);
2456 target->ToPlayer()->SendAttackSwingCancelAttack(); // melee and ranged forced attack cancel
2457 }
2458 else
2459 {
2460 target->CombatStop();
2461 target->getHostileRefMgr().deleteReferences();
2462 }
2463
2464 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
2465
2466 // prevent interrupt message
2467 if (GetCasterGUID() == target->GetGUID())
2468 {
2469 if (target->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL))
2470 target->FinishSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL, true);
2471
2472 // interrupt autoshot
2473 if (target->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL))
2474 {
2475 target->FinishSpell(CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL);
2476 target->ToPlayer()->SendAutoRepeatCancel(target);
2477 }
2478 }
2479
2480 target->InterruptNonMeleeSpells(true);
2481
2482 // stop handling the effect if it was removed by linked event
2483 if (aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
2484 return;
2485 // blizz like 2.0.x
2486 target->SetUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_PREVENT_EMOTES_FROM_CHAT_TEXT);
2487 // blizz like 2.0.x
2488 target->SetUnitFlag2(UNIT_FLAG2_FEIGN_DEATH);
2489 // blizz like 2.0.x
2490 target->SetDynamicFlag(UNIT_DYNFLAG_DEAD);
2491
2492 target->AddUnitState(UNIT_STATE_DIED);
2493 }
2494 else
2495 {
2496 /*
2497 WorldPacket data(SMSG_FEIGN_DEATH_RESISTED, 9);
2498 data<<target->GetGUID();
2499 data<<uint8(1);
2500 target->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
2501 */
2502 // blizz like 2.0.x
2503 target->RemoveUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_PREVENT_EMOTES_FROM_CHAT_TEXT);
2504 // blizz like 2.0.x
2505 target->RemoveUnitFlag2(UNIT_FLAG2_FEIGN_DEATH);
2506 // blizz like 2.0.x
2507 target->RemoveDynamicFlag(UNIT_DYNFLAG_DEAD);
2508
2509 target->ClearUnitState(UNIT_STATE_DIED);
2510 }
2511}
2512
2513void AuraEffect::HandleModUnattackable(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2514{
2515 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2516 return;
2517
2518 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2519
2520 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit
2521 if (!apply && target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_UNATTACKABLE))
2522 return;
2523
2524 target->ApplyModFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE, apply);
2525
2526 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
2527 if (apply && (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2528 {
2529 // xinef: this aura should not stop combat (movie with sindragosa proves that)
2530 //target->CombatStop();
2531 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_IMMUNE_OR_LOST_SELECTION);
2532 }
2533}
2534
2535void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModDisarm(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2536{
2537 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2538 return;
2539
2540 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2541
2542 AuraType type = GetAuraType();
2543
2544 //Prevent handling aura twice
2545 if ((apply) ? target->GetAuraEffectsByType(type).size() > 1 : target->HasAuraType(type))
2546 return;
2547
2548 uint32 field, flag, slot;
2549 WeaponAttackType attType;
2550 switch (type)
2551 {
2552 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM:
2553 field = UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS;
2554 flag = UNIT_FLAG_DISARMED;
2555 slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND;
2556 attType = BASE_ATTACK;
2557 break;
2558 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM_OFFHAND:
2559 field = UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2;
2560 flag = UNIT_FLAG2_DISARM_OFFHAND;
2561 slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND;
2562 attType = OFF_ATTACK;
2563 break;
2564 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM_RANGED:
2565 field = UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2;
2566 flag = UNIT_FLAG2_DISARM_RANGED;
2567 slot = EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED;
2568 attType = RANGED_ATTACK;
2569 break;
2570 default:
2571 return;
2572 }
2573
2574 // if disarm aura is to be removed, remove the flag first to reapply damage/aura mods
2575 if (!apply)
2576 target->RemoveFlag(field, flag);
2577
2578 // Handle damage modification, shapeshifted druids are not affected
2579 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (!target->IsInFeralForm() || target->GetShapeshiftForm() == FORM_GHOSTWOLF))
2580 {
2581 if (Item* pItem = target->ToPlayer()->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, slot))
2582 {
2583 uint8 attacktype = Player::GetAttackBySlot(slot);
2584
2585 if (attacktype < MAX_ATTACK)
2586 {
2587 target->ToPlayer()->_ApplyWeaponDamage(slot, pItem->GetTemplate(), nullptr, !apply);
2588 target->ToPlayer()->_ApplyWeaponDependentAuraMods(pItem, WeaponAttackType(attacktype), !apply);
2589 }
2590 }
2591 }
2592
2593 // if disarm effects should be applied, wait to set flag until damage mods are unapplied
2594 if (apply)
2595 target->SetFlag(field, flag);
2596
2597 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && target->ToCreature()->GetCurrentEquipmentId())
2598 target->UpdateDamagePhysical(attType);
2599}
2600
2601void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModSilence(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2602{
2603 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
2604 return;
2605
2606 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2607
2608 if (apply)
2609 {
2610 target->SetUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED);
2611
2612 // call functions which may have additional effects after chainging state of unit
2613 // Stop cast only spells vs PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE
2614 for (uint32 i = CURRENT_MELEE_SPELL; i < CURRENT_MAX_SPELL; ++i)
2615 if (Spell* spell = target->GetCurrentSpell(CurrentSpellTypes(i)))
2616 if (spell->m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE)
2617 // Stop spells on prepare or casting state
2618 target->InterruptSpell(CurrentSpellTypes(i), false);
2619 }
2620 else
2621 {
2622 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit
2623 if (target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SILENCE) || target->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE))
2624 return;
2625
2626 target->RemoveUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED);
2627 }
2628}
2629

2640 //target->AttackStop(); // pussywizard: why having this flag prevents from being in combat? it should just prevent melee attack
2641 }
2642 else
2643 {
2644 // do not remove unit flag if there are more than this auraEffect of that kind on unit on unit

2802void AuraEffect::HandleAuraModSkill(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2803{
2804 if (!(mode & (AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK | AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SKILL)))
2805 return;
2806 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2807
2808 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
2809 return;
2810
2811 uint32 prot = GetMiscValue();
2812 int32 points = GetAmount();
2813
2814 target->ToPlayer()->ModifySkillBonus(prot, ((apply) ? points : -points), GetAuraType() == SPELL_AURA_MOD_SKILL_TALENT);
2815 if (prot == SKILL_DEFENSE)
2816 target->ToPlayer()->UpdateDefenseBonusesMod();
2817}

2819/****************************/
2820/*** MOVEMENT ***/
2821/****************************/
2822
2823void AuraEffect::HandleAuraMounted(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
2824{
2825 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_SEND_FOR_CLIENT_MASK))
2826 return;
2827
2828 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
2829 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2830
2831 if (apply)
2832 {
2833 uint32 creatureEntry = GetMiscValue();
2834 uint32 displayId = 0;
2835 uint32 vehicleId = 0;
2836
2837 // Festive Holiday Mount
2838 if (target->HasAura(62061))
2839 {
2840 if (GetBase()->HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED))
2841 creatureEntry = 24906;
2842 else
2843 creatureEntry = 15665;
2844 }
2845
2846 // Festive Brewfest Mount
2847 if (!GetBase()->HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED) && target->HasAura(FRESH_BREWFEST_HOPS))
2848 {
2849 if (caster->GetSpeedRate(MOVE_RUN) >= 2.0f)
2850 {
2851 creatureEntry = GREAT_BREWFEST_KODO;
2852 }
2853 else
2854 {
2855 creatureEntry = BREWFEST_KODO;
2856 }
2857 }
2858
2859 if (CreatureTemplate const* creatureInfo = sObjectMgr->GetCreatureTemplate(creatureEntry))
2860 {
2861 if (GetMiscValueB() > 0) // Choose proper modelid
2862 {
2863 displayId = GetMiscValueB() == 2 && creatureInfo->Modelid2 > 0 ? creatureInfo->Modelid2 : creatureInfo->Modelid1;
2864 }
2865 else // Should we choose random modelid in this case?
2866 {
2867 displayId = ObjectMgr::ChooseDisplayId(creatureInfo);
2868 }
2869 sObjectMgr->GetCreatureModelRandomGender(&displayId);
2870
2871 vehicleId = creatureInfo->VehicleId;
2872
2873 //some spell has one aura of mount and one of vehicle
2874 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2875 {
2876 if (GetSpellInfo()->Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON && GetSpellInfo()->Effects[i].MiscValue == GetMiscValue())
2877 {
2878 displayId = 0;
2879 }
2880 }
2881
2882 }
2883 target->Mount(displayId, vehicleId, GetMiscValue());
2884 }
2885 else
2886 {
2887 target->Dismount();
2888 //some mounts like Headless Horseman's Mount or broom stick are skill based spell
2889 // need to remove ALL arura related to mounts, this will stop client crash with broom stick
2890 // and never endless flying after using Headless Horseman's Mount
2891 if (mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL)
2892 target->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED);
2893 }
2894}

3058 return;

3062 else

3064 // When taunt aura fades out, mob will switch to previous target if current has less than 1.1 * secondthreat
3065 target->TauntFadeOut(caster);
3066 }

3131void AuraEffect::HandleModPossess(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3132{
3133 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3134 return;
3135

3139

3141 if (caster && caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
3142 {
3143 HandleModCharm(aurApp, mode, apply);
3144 return;

3151}
3152
3153void AuraEffect::HandleModPossessPet(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3154{
3155 // Used by spell "Eyes of the Beast"
3156
3157 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3158 return;
3159
3160 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
3161 if (!caster || caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
3162 return;
3163
3164 //seems it may happen that when removing it is no longer owner's pet
3165 //if (caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet() != target)
3166 // return;
3167
3168 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3169 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_UNIT || !target->IsPet())
3170 return;
3171
3172 Pet* pet = target->ToPet();
3173
3174 if (apply)
3175 {
3176 if (caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet() != pet)
3177 return;
3178
3179 // Must clear current motion or pet leashes back to owner after a few yards
3180 // when under spell 'Eyes of the Beast'
3181 pet->GetMotionMaster()->Clear();
3182 pet->SetCharmedBy(caster, CHARM_TYPE_POSSESS, aurApp);
3183 }
3184 else
3185 {
3186 pet->RemoveCharmedBy(caster);
3187
3188 if (!pet->IsWithinDistInMap(caster, pet->GetMap()->GetVisibilityRange()))
3189 pet->Remove(PET_SAVE_NOT_IN_SLOT, true);
3190 else
3191 {
3192 // Reinitialize the pet bar or it will appear greyed out
3193 caster->ToPlayer()->PetSpellInitialize();
3194
3195 // Follow owner only if not fighting or owner didn't click "stay" at new location
3196 // This may be confusing because pet bar shows "stay" when under the spell but it retains
3197 // the "follow" flag. Player MUST click "stay" while under the spell.
3198 if (!pet->GetVictim() && !pet->GetCharmInfo()->HasCommandState(COMMAND_STAY))
3199 {
3200 pet->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(caster, PET_FOLLOW_DIST, pet->GetFollowAngle());
3201 }
3202 }
3203 }
3204}
3205
3206void AuraEffect::HandleModCharm(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3207{
3208 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3209 return;
3210
3211 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3212
3213 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
3214
3215 if (apply)
3216 target->SetCharmedBy(caster, CHARM_TYPE_CHARM, aurApp);
3217 else
3218 target->RemoveCharmedBy(caster);
3219}
3220
3221void AuraEffect::HandleCharmConvert(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3222{
3223 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL))
3224 return;
3225
3226 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3227
3228 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
3229
3230 if (apply)
3231 target->SetCharmedBy(caster, CHARM_TYPE_CONVERT, aurApp);
3232 else
3233 target->RemoveCharmedBy(caster);
3234}
3235
3240void AuraEffect::HandleAuraControlVehicle(AuraApplication const* aurApp, uint8 mode, bool apply) const
3241{
3242 if (!(mode & AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK))
3243 return;
3244
3245 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
3246
3247 if (!target->IsVehicle())
3248 return;
3249
3250 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
3251
3252 if (!caster || caster == target)
3253 return;
3254
3255 if (apply)
3256 {
3257 // Currently spells that have base points 0 and DieSides 0 = "0/0" exception are pushed to -1,
3258 // however the idea of 0/0 is to ingore flag VEHICLE_SEAT_FLAG_CAN_ENTER_OR_EXIT and -1 checks for it,
3259 // so this break such spells or most of them.
3260 // Current formula about m_amount: effect base points + dieside - 1
3261 // TO DO: Reasearch more about 0/0 and fix it.
3262 caster->_EnterVehicle(target->GetVehicleKit(), m_amount - 1, aurApp);
3263 }
3264 else
3265 {
3266 if (GetId() == 53111) // Devour Humanoid
3267 {
3268 Unit::Kill(target, caster);
3269 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
3270 caster->ToCreature()->RemoveCorpse();
3271 }
3272
3273 caster->_ExitVehicle();
3274 // some SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE auras have a dummy effect on the player - remove them
3275 caster->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(GetId());
3276 }
3277}

3281/*********************************************************/

3290

3292 {
3293 sScriptMgr->AnticheatSetUnderACKmount(targetPlayer);
3294 }
3295}
