5822}
5823
5824void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicDummyAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
5825{
5826 switch (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName)
5827 {
5828 case SPELLFAMILY_DRUID:
5829 {
5830 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
5831 {
5832 // Frenzied Regeneration
5833 case 22842:
5834 {
5835 // Converts up to 10 rage per second into health for $d. Each point of rage is converted into ${$m2/10}.1% of max health.
5836 // Should be manauser
5837 if (target->getPowerType() != POWER_RAGE)
5838 break;
5839 uint32 rage = target->GetPower(POWER_RAGE);
5840 // Nothing todo
5841 if (rage == 0)
5842 break;
5843 int32 mod = (rage < 100) ? rage : 100;
5844 int32 points = target->CalculateSpellDamage(target, GetSpellInfo(), 1);
5845 int32 regen = target->GetMaxHealth() * (mod * points / 10) / 1000;
5846 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 22845, &regen, 0, 0, true, 0, this);
5847 target->SetPower(POWER_RAGE, rage - mod);
5848 break;
5849 }
5850 }
5851 break;
5852 }
5853 case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
5854 {
5855 // Explosive Shot
5856 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x80000000)
5857 {
5858 if (caster)
5859 caster->CastCustomSpell(53352, SPELLVALUE_BASE_POINT0, m_amount, target, true, nullptr, this);
5860 break;
5861 }
5862 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
5863 {
5864 // Feeding Frenzy Rank 1
5865 case 53511:
5866 if (target->GetVictim() && target->GetVictim()->HealthBelowPct(35))
5867 target->CastSpell(target, 60096, true, 0, this);
5868 return;
5869 // Feeding Frenzy Rank 2
5870 case 53512:
5871 if (target->GetVictim() && target->GetVictim()->HealthBelowPct(35))
5872 target->CastSpell(target, 60097, true, 0, this);
5873 return;
5874 default:
5875 break;
5876 }
5877 break;
5878 }
5879 case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
5880 if (GetId() == 52179) // Astral Shift
5881 {
5882 // Periodic need for remove visual on stun/fear/silence lost
5883 if (!(target->GetUnitFlags() & (UNIT_FLAG_STUNNED | UNIT_FLAG_FLEEING | UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED)))
5884 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(52179);
5885 break;
5886 }
5887 break;
5888 case SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT:
5889 switch (GetId())
5890 {
5891 case 49016: // Hysteria
5892 uint32 damage = uint32(target->CountPctFromMaxHealth(1));
5893 Unit::DealDamage(target, target, damage, nullptr, NODAMAGE, SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_NORMAL, nullptr, false);
5894 break;
5895 }
5896 // Blood of the North
5897 // Reaping
5898 // Death Rune Mastery
5899 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellIconID == 3041 || GetSpellInfo()->SpellIconID == 22 || GetSpellInfo()->SpellIconID == 2622)
5900 {
5901 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5902 return;
5903 if (target->ToPlayer()->getClass() != CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
5904 return;
5905
5906 // timer expired - remove death runes
5907 target->ToPlayer()->RemoveRunesByAuraEffect(this);
5908 }
5909 break;
5910 default:
5911 break;
5912 }
5913}
5914
5915void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
5916{
5917 // generic casting code with custom spells and target/caster customs
5918 uint32 triggerSpellId = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].TriggerSpell;
5919
5920 SpellInfo const* triggeredSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(triggerSpellId);
5921 SpellInfo const* auraSpellInfo = GetSpellInfo();
5922 uint32 auraId = auraSpellInfo->Id;
5923
5924 // specific code for cases with no trigger spell provided in field
5925 if (!triggeredSpellInfo)
5926 {
5927 switch (auraSpellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
5928 {
5929 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
5930 {
5931 switch (auraId)
5932 {
5933 // Thaumaturgy Channel
5934 case 9712:
5935 triggerSpellId = 21029;
5936 if (caster)
5937 caster->CastSpell(caster, triggerSpellId, true);
5938 return;
5939 // Brood Affliction: Bronze
5940 case 23170:
5941 // Only 10% chance of triggering spell
5942 if (roll_chance_f(10.f))
5943 {
5944 triggerSpellId = 23171;
5945 }
5946 break;
5947 // Restoration
5948 case 24379:
5949 case 23493:
5950 {
5951 if (caster)
5952 {
5953 int32 heal = caster->CountPctFromMaxHealth(10);
5954 HealInfo healInfo(caster, target, heal, auraSpellInfo, auraSpellInfo->GetSchoolMask());
5955 caster->HealBySpell(healInfo);
5956
5957 if (int32 mana = caster->GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA))
5958 {
5959 mana /= 10;
5960 caster->EnergizeBySpell(caster, 23493, mana, POWER_MANA);
5961 }
5962 }
5963 return;
5964 }
5965 // Nitrous Boost
5966 case 27746:
5967 if (caster && target->GetPower(POWER_MANA) >= 10)
5968 {
5969 target->ModifyPower(POWER_MANA, -10);
5970 target->SendEnergizeSpellLog(caster, 27746, 10, POWER_MANA);
5971 }
5972 else
5973 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(27746);
5974 return;
5975 // Frost Blast
5976 case 27808:
5977 if (caster)
5978 {
5979 caster->CastCustomSpell(29879, SPELLVALUE_BASE_POINT0, int32(target->CountPctFromMaxHealth(21)), target, true, nullptr, this);
5980 if (GetTickNumber() == 1)
5981 caster->CastSpell(target, 27808, true);
5982 }
5983 return;
5984 // Inoculate Nestlewood Owlkin
5985 case 29528:
5986 if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_UNIT) // prevent error reports in case ignored player target
5987 return;
5988 break;
5989 // Feed Captured Animal
5990 case 29917:
5991 triggerSpellId = 29916;
5992 break;
5993 // Extract Gas
5994 case 30427:
5995 {
5996 // move loot to player inventory and despawn target
5997 if (caster && caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER &&
5998 target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT &&
5999 target->ToCreature()->GetCreatureTemplate()->type == CREATURE_TYPE_GAS_CLOUD)
6000 {
6001 Player* player = caster->ToPlayer();
6002 Creature* creature = target->ToCreature();
6003 // missing lootid has been reported on startup - just return
6004 if (!creature->GetCreatureTemplate()->SkinLootId)
6005 return;
6006
6007 player->AutoStoreLoot(creature->GetCreatureTemplate()->SkinLootId, LootTemplates_Skinning, true);
6008
6009 creature->DespawnOrUnsummon();
6010 }
6011 return;
6012 }
6013 // Quake
6014 case 30576:
6015 triggerSpellId = 30571;
6016 break;
6017 // Doom
6018 // TODO: effect trigger spell may be independant on spell targets, and executed in spell finish phase
6019 // so instakill will be naturally done before trigger spell
6020 case 31347:
6021 {
6022 target->CastSpell(target, 31350, true, nullptr, this);
6023 Unit::Kill(target, target);
6024 return;
6025 }
6026 // Spellcloth
6027 case 31373:
6028 {
6029 // Summon Elemental after create item
6030 target->SummonCreature(17870, 0, 0, 0, target->GetOrientation(), TEMPSUMMON_DEAD_DESPAWN, 0);
6031 return;
6032 }
6033 // Eye of Grillok
6034 case 38495:
6035 triggerSpellId = 38530;
6036 break;
6037 // Absorb Eye of Grillok (Zezzak's Shard)
6038 case 38554:
6039 {
6040 if (!caster || target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_UNIT)
6041 return;
6042
6043 caster->CastSpell(caster, 38495, true, nullptr, this);
6044
6045 Creature* creatureTarget = target->ToCreature();
6046
6047 creatureTarget->DespawnOrUnsummon();
6048 return;
6049 }
6050 // Tear of Azzinoth Summon Channel - it's not really supposed to do anything, and this only prevents the console spam
6051 case 39857:
6052 triggerSpellId = 39856;
6053 break;
6054 // Personalized Weather
6055 case 46736:
6056 triggerSpellId = 46737;
6057 break;
6058 // Shield Level 1
6059 case 63130:
6060 // Shield Level 2
6061 case 63131:
6062 // Shield Level 3
6063 case 63132:
6064 // Ball of Flames Visual
6065 case 71706:
6066 return;
6067 // Oculus, Mage-Lord Urom, Time Bomb
6068 case 51121:
6069 case 59376:
6070 {
6071 const int32 dmg = target->GetMaxHealth() - target->GetHealth();
6072 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 51132, &dmg, 0, 0, true);
6073 return;
6074 }
6075 }
6076 break;
6077 }
6078 case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
6079 {
6080 switch (auraId)
6081 {
6082 // Lightning Shield (The Earthshatterer set trigger after cast Lighting Shield)
6083 case 28820:
6084 {
6085 // Need remove self if Lightning Shield not active
6086 if (!target->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL, SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN, 0x400, 0, 0))
6087 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(28820);
6088 return;
6089 }
6090 }
6091 break;
6092 }
6093 default:
6094 break;
6095 }
6096 }
6097 else
6098 {
6099 // Spell exist but require custom code
6100 switch (auraId)
6101 {
6102 // Mana Tide
6103 case 16191:
6104 target->CastCustomSpell(target, triggerSpellId, &m_amount, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, this);
6105 return;
6106 // Poison (Grobbulus)
6107 case 28158:
6108 case 54362:
6109 // Slime Pool (Dreadscale & Acidmaw)
6110 case 66882:
6111 target->CastCustomSpell(triggerSpellId, SPELLVALUE_RADIUS_MOD, (int32)((((float)m_tickNumber / 60) * 0.9f + 0.1f) * 10000 * 2 / 3), nullptr, true, nullptr, this);
6112 return;
6113 // Eye of Eternity, Malygos, Arcane Overload
6114 case 56432:
6115 if (triggerSpellId == 56438)
6116 {
6117 target->CastCustomSpell(triggerSpellId, SPELLVALUE_RADIUS_MOD, (int32)(10000 * (1.0f - 0.02f * (m_tickNumber + 1))), nullptr, true, nullptr, this);
6118 return;
6119 }
6120 break;
6121 // Beacon of Light
6122 case 53563:
6123 {
6124 // area aura owner casts the spell
6125 GetBase()->GetUnitOwner()->CastSpell(target, triggeredSpellInfo, true, 0, this, GetBase()->GetUnitOwner()->GetGUID());
6126 return;
6127 }
6128 // Slime Spray - temporary here until preventing default effect works again
6129 // added on 9.10.2010
6130 case 69508:
6131 {
6132 if (caster)
6133 caster->CastSpell(target, triggerSpellId, true, nullptr, nullptr, caster->GetGUID());
6134 return;
6135 }
6136 // Trial of the Crusader, Jaraxxus, Spinning Pain Spike
6137 case 66283:
6138 {
6139 const int32 dmg = target->GetMaxHealth() / 2;
6140 target->CastCustomSpell(target, 66316, &dmg, nullptr, nullptr, true);
6141 return;
6142 }
6143 // Violet Hold, Moragg, Ray of Suffering, Ray of Pain
6144 case 54442:
6145 case 59524:
6146 case 54438:
6147 case 59523:
6148 {
6149 if (caster)
6150 if (Unit* victim = caster->GetVictim())
6151 if(victim->GetDistance(caster) < 45.0f)
6152 {
6153 target = victim;
6154 break;
6155 }
6156 return;
6157 }
6158 case 24745: // Summon Templar, Trigger
6159 case 24747: // Summon Templar Fire, Trigger
6160 case 24757: // Summon Templar Air, Trigger
6161 case 24759: // Summon Templar Earth, Trigger
6162 case 24761: // Summon Templar Water, Trigger
6163 case 24762: // Summon Duke, Trigger
6164 case 24766: // Summon Duke Fire, Trigger
6165 case 24769: // Summon Duke Air, Trigger
6166 case 24771: // Summon Duke Earth, Trigger
6167 case 24773: // Summon Duke Water, Trigger
6168 case 24785: // Summon Royal, Trigger
6169 case 24787: // Summon Royal Fire, Trigger
6170 case 24791: // Summon Royal Air, Trigger
6171 case 24792: // Summon Royal Earth, Trigger
6172 case 24793: // Summon Royal Water, Trigger
6173 {
6174 // All this spells trigger a spell that requires reagents; if the
6175 // triggered spell is cast as "triggered", reagents are not consumed
6176 if (caster)
6177 caster->CastSpell(target, triggerSpellId, false);
6178 return;
6179 }
6180 // Hunter - Rapid Recuperation
6181 case 56654:
6182 case 58882:
6183 int32 amount = int32(target->GetMaxPower(POWER_MANA) * GetAmount() / 100.0f);
6184 target->CastCustomSpell(target, triggerSpellId, &amount, nullptr, nullptr, true);
6185 return;
6186 }
6187 }
6188
6189 // Reget trigger spell proto
6190 triggeredSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(triggerSpellId);
6191
6192 if (triggeredSpellInfo)
6193 {
6194 if (Unit* triggerCaster = triggeredSpellInfo->NeedsToBeTriggeredByCaster(m_spellInfo, GetEffIndex()) ? caster : target)
6195 {
6196 SpellCastTargets targets;
6197 targets.SetUnitTarget(target);
6198 if (triggeredSpellInfo->IsChannelCategorySpell() && m_channelData)
6199 {
6200 targets.SetDstChannel(m_channelData->spellDst);
6201 targets.SetObjectTargetChannel(m_channelData->channelGUID);
6202 }
6203
6204 // Xinef: do not skip reagent cost for entry casts
6205 TriggerCastFlags triggerFlags = TRIGGERED_FULL_MASK;
6206 if (GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].TargetA.GetCheckType() == TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY || GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].TargetB.GetCheckType() == TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY)
6207 triggerFlags = TriggerCastFlags(TRIGGERED_FULL_MASK & ~TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST);
6208
6209 triggerCaster->CastSpell(targets, triggeredSpellInfo, nullptr, triggerFlags, nullptr, this);
6210 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellAuraTick: Spell {} Trigger {}", GetId(), triggeredSpellInfo->Id);
6211 }
6212 }
6213}
6214
6215void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellWithValueAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6216{
6217 uint32 triggerSpellId = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[m_effIndex].TriggerSpell;
6218 if (SpellInfo const* triggeredSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(triggerSpellId))
6219 {
6220 if (Unit* triggerCaster = triggeredSpellInfo->NeedsToBeTriggeredByCaster(m_spellInfo, GetEffIndex()) ? caster : target)
6221 {
6222 SpellCastTargets targets;
6223 targets.SetUnitTarget(target);
6224 if (triggeredSpellInfo->IsChannelCategorySpell() && m_channelData)
6225 {
6226 targets.SetDstChannel(m_channelData->spellDst);
6227 targets.SetObjectTargetChannel(m_channelData->channelGUID);
6228 }
6229
6230 CustomSpellValues values;
6231 values.AddSpellMod(SPELLVALUE_BASE_POINT0, GetAmount());
6232
6233 triggerCaster->CastSpell(targets, triggeredSpellInfo, &values, TRIGGERED_FULL_MASK, nullptr, this);
6234 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellWithValueAuraTick: Spell {} Trigger {}", GetId(), triggeredSpellInfo->Id);
6235 }
6236 }
6237 else
6238 {
6239 Creature* c = target->ToCreature();
6240 if (c && caster)
6241 {
6242 sScriptMgr->OnDummyEffect(caster, GetId(), SpellEffIndex(GetEffIndex()), target->ToCreature());
6243 }
6244
6245 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicTriggerSpellWithValueAuraTick: Spell {} has non-existent spell {} in EffectTriggered[{}] and is therefor not triggered.", GetId(), triggerSpellId, GetEffIndex());
6246 }
6247}
6248
6249void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicDamageAurasTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6250{
6251 if (!target->IsAlive())
6252 return;
6253
6254 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED) || target->IsImmunedToDamageOrSchool(GetSpellInfo()) || target->IsTotem())
6255 {
6256 SendTickImmune(target, caster);
6257 return;
6258 }
6259
6260 // Consecrate ticks can miss and will not show up in the combat log
6261 if (caster && GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA &&
6262 caster->SpellHitResult(target, GetSpellInfo(), false) != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6263 return;
6264
6265 // some auras remove at specific health level or more
6266 if (GetAuraType() == SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE)
6267 {
6268 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
6269 {
6270 case 43093:
6271 case 31956:
6272 case 38801: // Grievous Wound
6273 case 35321:
6274 case 38363:
6275 case 39215: // Gushing Wound
6276 if (target->IsFullHealth())
6277 {
6278 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(GetSpellInfo()->Id);
6279 return;
6280 }
6281 break;
6282 case 38772: // Grievous Wound
6283 {
6284 uint32 percent = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[EFFECT_1].CalcValue(caster);
6285 if (!target->HealthBelowPct(percent))
6286 {
6287 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(GetSpellInfo()->Id);
6288 return;
6289 }
6290 break;
6291 }
6292 }
6293 }
6294
6295 CleanDamage cleanDamage = CleanDamage(0, 0, BASE_ATTACK, MELEE_HIT_NORMAL);
6296
6297 // ignore non positive values (can be result apply spellmods to aura damage
6298 uint32 damage = std::max(GetAmount(), 0);
6299
6300 // Script Hook For HandlePeriodicDamageAurasTick -- Allow scripts to change the Damage pre class mitigation calculations
6301 sScriptMgr->ModifyPeriodicDamageAurasTick(target, caster, damage);
6302
6303 if (GetAuraType() == SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE)
6304 {
6305 // xinef: leave only target depending bonuses, rest is handled in calculate amount
6306 if (GetBase()->GetType() == DYNOBJ_AURA_TYPE && caster)
6307 damage = caster->SpellDamageBonusDone(target, GetSpellInfo(), damage, DOT, GetEffIndex(), 0.0f, GetBase()->GetStackAmount());
6308 damage = target->SpellDamageBonusTaken(caster, GetSpellInfo(), damage, DOT, GetBase()->GetStackAmount());
6309
6310 // Calculate armor mitigation
6311 if (Unit::IsDamageReducedByArmor(GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), GetSpellInfo(), GetEffIndex()))
6312 {
6313 uint32 damageReductedArmor = Unit::CalcArmorReducedDamage(caster, target, damage, GetSpellInfo(), GetCasterLevel());
6314 cleanDamage.mitigated_damage += damage - damageReductedArmor;
6315 damage = damageReductedArmor;
6316 }
6317
6318 // Curse of Agony damage-per-tick calculation
6319 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK && (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400) && GetSpellInfo()->SpellIconID == 544)
6320 {
6321 uint32 totalTick = GetTotalTicks();
6322 // 1..4 ticks, 1/2 from normal tick damage
6323 if (m_tickNumber <= totalTick / 3)
6324 damage = damage / 2;
6325 // 9..12 ticks, 3/2 from normal tick damage
6326 else if (m_tickNumber > totalTick * 2 / 3)
6327 damage += (damage + 1) / 2; // +1 prevent 0.5 damage possible lost at 1..4 ticks
6328 // 5..8 ticks have normal tick damage
6329 }
6330 }
6331 else // xinef: ceil obtained value, it may happen that 10 ticks for 10% damage may not kill owner
6332 damage = uint32(std::ceil(CalculatePct<float, float>(target->GetMaxHealth(), damage)));
6333
6334 // calculate crit chance
6335 bool crit = false;
6336 if ((crit = roll_chance_f(GetCritChance())))
6337 damage = Unit::SpellCriticalDamageBonus(caster, m_spellInfo, damage, target);
6338
6339 // Auras reducing damage from AOE spells
6340 if (GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].IsAreaAuraEffect() || GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].IsTargetingArea() || GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA) // some persistent area auras have targets like A=53 B=28
6341 {
6342 damage = target->CalculateAOEDamageReduction(damage, GetSpellInfo()->SchoolMask, caster);
6343 }
6344
6345 int32 dmg = damage;
6346 int32 mitigatedDamage = cleanDamage.mitigated_damage;
6347 if (CanApplyResilience())
6348 {
6349 int32 resilienceReduction = dmg;
6350 Unit::ApplyResilience(target, nullptr, &resilienceReduction, crit, CR_CRIT_TAKEN_SPELL);
6351
6352 resilienceReduction = dmg - resilienceReduction;
6353 dmg -= resilienceReduction;
6354 mitigatedDamage += resilienceReduction;
6355 }
6356
6357 damage = std::max(0, dmg);
6358 cleanDamage.mitigated_damage = std::max(0, mitigatedDamage);
6359
6360 DamageInfo dmgInfo(caster, target, damage, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), DOT, cleanDamage.mitigated_damage);
6361 Unit::CalcAbsorbResist(dmgInfo);
6362
6363 uint32 absorb = dmgInfo.GetAbsorb();
6364 uint32 resist = dmgInfo.GetResist();
6365 damage = dmgInfo.GetDamage();
6366
6367 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura.effect", "PeriodicTick: {} attacked {} for {} dmg inflicted by {} abs is {}",
6368 GetCasterGUID().ToString(), target->GetGUID().ToString(), damage, GetId(), absorb);
6369 Unit::DealDamageMods(target, damage, &absorb);
6370
6371 // Set trigger flag
6372 uint32 procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_PERIODIC;
6373 uint32 procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_PERIODIC;
6374 uint32 procEx = (crit ? PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT : PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT) | PROC_EX_INTERNAL_DOT;
6375 if (absorb > 0)
6376 procEx |= PROC_EX_ABSORB;
6377
6378 if (damage)
6379 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_DAMAGE;
6380
6381 int32 overkill = damage - target->GetHealth();
6382 if (overkill < 0)
6383 overkill = 0;
6384
6385 SpellPeriodicAuraLogInfo pInfo(this, damage, overkill, absorb, resist, 0.0f, crit);
6386 target->SendPeriodicAuraLog(&pInfo);
6387
6388 Unit::DealDamage(caster, target, damage, &cleanDamage, DOT, GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), GetSpellInfo(), true);
6389
6390 Unit::ProcDamageAndSpell(caster, target, caster ? procAttacker : 0, procVictim, procEx, damage, BASE_ATTACK, GetSpellInfo(), nullptr, GetEffIndex(), nullptr, &dmgInfo);
6391}
6392
6393void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicHealthLeechAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6394{
6395 if (!target->IsAlive())
6396 return;
6397
6398 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED) || target->IsImmunedToDamageOrSchool(GetSpellInfo()))
6399 {
6400 SendTickImmune(target, caster);
6401 return;
6402 }
6403
6404 if (caster && GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA &&
6405 caster->SpellHitResult(target, GetSpellInfo(), false) != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6406 return;
6407
6408 CleanDamage cleanDamage = CleanDamage(0, 0, BASE_ATTACK, MELEE_HIT_NORMAL);
6409
6410 uint32 damage = std::max(GetAmount(), 0);
6411
6412 // Script Hook For HandlePeriodicHealthLeechAurasTick -- Allow scripts to change the Damage pre class mitigation calculations
6413 sScriptMgr->ModifyPeriodicDamageAurasTick(target, caster, damage);
6414
6415 if (GetBase()->GetType() == DYNOBJ_AURA_TYPE)
6416 damage = caster->SpellDamageBonusDone(target, GetSpellInfo(), damage, DOT, GetEffIndex(), 0.0f, GetBase()->GetStackAmount());
6417 damage = target->SpellDamageBonusTaken(caster, GetSpellInfo(), damage, DOT, GetBase()->GetStackAmount());
6418
6419 bool crit = false;
6420 if ((crit = roll_chance_f(GetCritChance())))
6421 damage = Unit::SpellCriticalDamageBonus(caster, m_spellInfo, damage, target);
6422
6423 // Calculate armor mitigation
6424 if (Unit::IsDamageReducedByArmor(GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), GetSpellInfo(), m_effIndex))
6425 {
6426 uint32 damageReductedArmor = Unit::CalcArmorReducedDamage(caster, target, damage, GetSpellInfo(), GetCasterLevel());
6427 cleanDamage.mitigated_damage += damage - damageReductedArmor;
6428 damage = damageReductedArmor;
6429 }
6430
6431 int32 dmg = damage;
6432 int32 cleanDamageAmount = cleanDamage.mitigated_damage;
6433 if (CanApplyResilience())
6434 {
6435 int32 resilienceReduction = dmg;
6436 Unit::ApplyResilience(target, nullptr, &resilienceReduction, crit, CR_CRIT_TAKEN_SPELL);
6437
6438 resilienceReduction = dmg - resilienceReduction;
6439 dmg -= resilienceReduction;
6440 cleanDamageAmount += resilienceReduction;
6441 }
6442
6443 damage = std::max(0, dmg);
6444 cleanDamage.mitigated_damage = std::max(0, cleanDamageAmount);
6445
6446 DamageInfo dmgInfo(caster, target, damage, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), DOT, cleanDamage.mitigated_damage);
6447 Unit::CalcAbsorbResist(dmgInfo);
6448
6449 uint32 absorb = dmgInfo.GetAbsorb();
6450 uint32 resist = dmgInfo.GetResist();
6451 damage = dmgInfo.GetDamage();
6452
6453 // Set trigger flag
6454 uint32 procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_PERIODIC;
6455 uint32 procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_PERIODIC;
6456 uint32 procEx = (crit ? PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT : PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT) | PROC_EX_INTERNAL_DOT;
6457 if (absorb > 0)
6458 procEx |= PROC_EX_ABSORB;
6459
6460 if (dmgInfo.GetDamage())
6461 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_DAMAGE;
6462
6463 if (target->GetHealth() < dmgInfo.GetDamage())
6464 {
6465 dmgInfo.ModifyDamage(dmgInfo.GetDamage() - target->GetHealth());
6466 }
6467
6468 damage = dmgInfo.GetDamage();
6469
6470 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura.effect", "PeriodicTick: {} health leech of {} for {} dmg inflicted by {} abs is {}",
6471 GetCasterGUID().ToString(), target->GetGUID().ToString(), damage, GetId(), absorb);
6472 if (caster)
6473 caster->SendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(target, GetSpellInfo(), damage, GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), absorb, resist, false, 0, crit);
6474
6475 int32 new_damage;
6476
6477 new_damage = Unit::DealDamage(caster, target, damage, &cleanDamage, DOT, GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), GetSpellInfo(), false);
6478
6479 Unit::ProcDamageAndSpell(caster, target, caster ? procAttacker : 0, procVictim, procEx, damage, BASE_ATTACK, GetSpellInfo(), nullptr, GetEffIndex(), nullptr, &dmgInfo);
6480
6481 if (!caster || !caster->IsAlive())
6482 return;
6483
6484 float gainMultiplier = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].CalcValueMultiplier(caster);
6485
6486 uint32 heal = uint32(caster->SpellHealingBonusDone(caster, GetSpellInfo(), uint32(new_damage * gainMultiplier), DOT, GetEffIndex(), 0.0f, GetBase()->GetStackAmount()));
6487 heal = uint32(caster->SpellHealingBonusTaken(caster, GetSpellInfo(), heal, DOT, GetBase()->GetStackAmount()));
6488
6489 HealInfo healInfo(caster, caster, heal, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask());
6490 int32 gain = caster->HealBySpell(healInfo);
6491 caster->getHostileRefMgr().threatAssist(caster, gain * 0.5f, GetSpellInfo());
6492}
6493
6494void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicHealthFunnelAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6495{
6496 if (!caster || !caster->IsAlive() || !target->IsAlive())
6497 return;
6498
6499 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED))
6500 {
6501 SendTickImmune(target, caster);
6502 return;
6503 }
6504
6505 uint32 damage = std::max(GetAmount(), 0);
6506 // do not kill health donator
6507 if (caster->GetHealth() < damage)
6508 damage = caster->GetHealth() - 1;
6509 if (!damage)
6510 return;
6511
6512 caster->ModifyHealth(-(int32)damage);
6513 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "PeriodicTick: donator {} target {} damage {}.", caster->GetEntry(), target->GetEntry(), damage);
6514
6515 float gainMultiplier = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].CalcValueMultiplier(caster);
6516
6517 damage = int32(damage * gainMultiplier);
6518
6519 HealInfo healInfo(caster, target, damage, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask());
6520 caster->HealBySpell(healInfo);
6521}
6522
6523void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicHealAurasTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6524{
6525 if (!target->IsAlive())
6526 return;
6527
6528 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED))
6529 {
6530 SendTickImmune(target, caster);
6531 return;
6532 }
6533
6534 // heal for caster damage (must be alive)
6535 if (target != caster && GetSpellInfo()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_NO_TARGET_PER_SECOND_COST) && (!caster || !caster->IsAlive()))
6536 return;
6537
6538 // don't regen when permanent aura target has full power
6539 if (GetBase()->IsPermanent() && target->IsFullHealth())
6540 return;
6541
6542 // ignore negative values (can be result apply spellmods to aura damage
6543 int32 damage = std::max(m_amount, 0);
6544
6545 if (GetAuraType() == SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH)
6546 {
6547 // Taken mods
6548 float TakenTotalMod = 1.0f;
6549
6550 // Tenacity increase healing % taken
6551 if (AuraEffect const* Tenacity = target->GetAuraEffect(58549, 0))
6552 AddPct(TakenTotalMod, Tenacity->GetAmount());
6553
6554 // Healing taken percent
6555 float minval = (float)target->GetMaxNegativeAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_PCT);
6556 if (minval)
6557 AddPct(TakenTotalMod, minval);
6558
6559 float maxval = (float)target->GetMaxPositiveAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_PCT);
6560 if (maxval)
6561 AddPct(TakenTotalMod, maxval);
6562
6563 // Healing over time taken percent
6564 float minval_hot = (float)target->GetMaxNegativeAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_HOT_PCT);
6565 if (minval_hot)
6566 AddPct(TakenTotalMod, minval_hot);
6567
6568 float maxval_hot = (float)target->GetMaxPositiveAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_HOT_PCT);
6569 if (maxval_hot)
6570 AddPct(TakenTotalMod, maxval_hot);
6571
6572 // Arena / BG Dampening
6573 float minval_pct = (float)target->GetMaxNegativeAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE_PERCENT);
6574 if (minval_pct)
6575 AddPct(TakenTotalMod, minval_pct);
6576
6577 TakenTotalMod = std::max(TakenTotalMod, 0.0f);
6578
6579 // the most ugly hack i made :P the other option is to change all spellvalues to float...
6580 // demonic aegis
6581 if (caster && GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK && (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x20000000))
6582 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = caster->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_ADD_PCT_MODIFIER, SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK, 89, 0))
6583 AddPct(TakenTotalMod, aurEff->GetAmount());
6584
6585 damage = uint32(target->CountPctFromMaxHealth(damage));
6586 damage = uint32(damage * TakenTotalMod);
6587 }
6588 else
6589 {
6590 // Wild Growth = amount + (6 - 2*doneTicks) * ticks* amount / 100
6591 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && GetSpellInfo()->SpellIconID == 2864)
6592 {
6593 uint32 tickNumber = GetTickNumber() - 1;
6594 int32 tempAmount = m_spellInfo->Effects[m_effIndex].CalcValue(caster, &m_baseAmount, nullptr);
6595
6596 float drop = 2.0f;
6597
6598 // Item - Druid T10 Restoration 2P Bonus
6599 if (caster)
6600 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = caster->GetAuraEffect(70658, 0))
6601 AddPct(drop, -aurEff->GetAmount());
6602
6603 damage += GetTotalTicks() * tempAmount * (6 - (drop * tickNumber)) * 0.01f;
6604 }
6605
6606 if (GetBase()->GetType() == DYNOBJ_AURA_TYPE)
6607 damage = caster->SpellHealingBonusDone(target, GetSpellInfo(), damage, DOT, GetEffIndex(), 0.0f, GetBase()->GetStackAmount());
6608 damage = target->SpellHealingBonusTaken(caster, GetSpellInfo(), damage, DOT, GetBase()->GetStackAmount());
6609 }
6610
6611 bool crit = false;
6612 if ((crit = roll_chance_f(GetCritChance())))
6613 damage = Unit::SpellCriticalHealingBonus(caster, GetSpellInfo(), damage, target);
6614
6615 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura.effect", "PeriodicTick: {} heal of {} for {} health inflicted by {}",
6616 GetCasterGUID().ToString(), target->GetGUID().ToString(), damage, GetId());
6617
6618 uint32 heal = uint32(damage);
6619
6620 // Script Hook For HandlePeriodicDamageAurasTick -- Allow scripts to change the Damage pre class mitigation calculations
6621 sScriptMgr->ModifyPeriodicDamageAurasTick(target, caster, heal);
6622 sScriptMgr->ModifyHealReceived(target, caster, heal, GetSpellInfo());
6623
6624 HealInfo healInfo(caster, target, heal, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask());
6625 Unit::CalcHealAbsorb(healInfo);
6626 int32 gain = Unit::DealHeal(caster, target, healInfo.GetHeal());
6627
6628 SpellPeriodicAuraLogInfo pInfo(this, healInfo.GetHeal(), healInfo.GetHeal() - gain, healInfo.GetAbsorb(), 0, 0.0f, crit);
6629 target->SendPeriodicAuraLog(&pInfo);
6630
6631 if (caster)
6632 target->getHostileRefMgr().threatAssist(caster, float(gain) * 0.5f, GetSpellInfo());
6633
6634 bool haveCastItem = GetBase()->GetCastItemGUID();
6635
6636 // Health Funnel
6637 // damage caster for heal amount
6638 // xinef: caster is available, checked earlier
6639 if (target != caster && GetSpellInfo()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_NO_TARGET_PER_SECOND_COST))
6640 {
6641 uint32 manaPerSecond = GetSpellInfo()->ManaPerSecond;
6642 if ((int32)manaPerSecond > gain && gain > 0)
6643 {
6644 manaPerSecond = gain;
6645 }
6646
6647 uint32 absorb2 = 0;
6648 Unit::DealDamageMods(caster, manaPerSecond, &absorb2);
6649
6650 CleanDamage cleanDamage = CleanDamage(0, 0, BASE_ATTACK, MELEE_HIT_NORMAL);
6651 Unit::DealDamage(caster, caster, manaPerSecond, &cleanDamage, SELF_DAMAGE, GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), GetSpellInfo(), true);
6652 }
6653
6654 uint32 procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_PERIODIC;
6655 uint32 procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_PERIODIC;
6656 uint32 procEx = (crit ? PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT : PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT) | PROC_EX_INTERNAL_HOT;
6657 if (healInfo.GetAbsorb() > 0)
6658 procEx |= PROC_EX_ABSORB;
6659
6660 // ignore item heals
6661 if (!haveCastItem && GetAuraType() != SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH) // xinef: dont allow obs_mod_health to proc spells, this is passive regeneration and not hot
6662 Unit::ProcDamageAndSpell(caster, target, caster ? procAttacker : 0, procVictim, procEx, heal, BASE_ATTACK, GetSpellInfo(), nullptr, GetEffIndex(), nullptr, nullptr, &healInfo);
6663}
6664
6665void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicManaLeechAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6666{
6667 Powers PowerType = Powers(GetMiscValue());
6668
6669 if (!caster || !caster->IsAlive() || !target->IsAlive() || target->getPowerType() != PowerType)
6670 return;
6671
6672 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED) || target->IsImmunedToDamageOrSchool(GetSpellInfo()))
6673 {
6674 SendTickImmune(target, caster);
6675 return;
6676 }
6677
6678 if (GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA &&
6679 caster->SpellHitResult(target, GetSpellInfo(), false) != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6680 return;
6681
6682 // ignore negative values (can be result apply spellmods to aura damage
6683 int32 drainAmount = std::max(m_amount, 0);
6684
6685 // Special case: draining x% of mana (up to a maximum of 2*x% of the caster's maximum mana)
6686 // It's mana percent cost spells, m_amount is percent drain from target
6687 if (m_spellInfo->ManaCostPercentage)
6688 {
6689 // max value
6690 int32 maxmana = CalculatePct(caster->GetMaxPower(PowerType), drainAmount * 2.0f);
6691 ApplyPct(drainAmount, target->GetMaxPower(PowerType));
6692 if (drainAmount > maxmana)
6693 drainAmount = maxmana;
6694 }
6695
6696 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura.effect", "PeriodicTick: {} power leech of {} for {} dmg inflicted by {}",
6697 GetCasterGUID().ToString(), target->GetGUID().ToString(), drainAmount, GetId());
6698 // resilience reduce mana draining effect at spell crit damage reduction (added in 2.4)
6699 if (PowerType == POWER_MANA)
6700 drainAmount -= target->GetSpellCritDamageReduction(drainAmount);
6701
6702 int32 drainedAmount = -target->ModifyPower(PowerType, -drainAmount);
6703
6704 float gainMultiplier = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].CalcValueMultiplier(caster);
6705
6706 SpellPeriodicAuraLogInfo pInfo(this, drainedAmount, 0, 0, 0, gainMultiplier, false);
6707 target->SendPeriodicAuraLog(&pInfo);
6708
6709 int32 gainAmount = int32(drainedAmount * gainMultiplier);
6710 int32 gainedAmount = 0;
6711 if (gainAmount)
6712 {
6713 gainedAmount = caster->ModifyPower(PowerType, gainAmount);
6714 target->AddThreat(caster, float(gainedAmount) * 0.5f, GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), GetSpellInfo());
6715 }
6716
6717 target->AddThreat(caster, float(gainedAmount) * 0.5f, GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask(), GetSpellInfo());
6718
6719 // remove CC auras
6720 target->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_TAKE_DAMAGE);
6721
6722 // Drain Mana
6723 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK
6724 && m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00000010)
6725 {
6726 int32 manaFeedVal = 0;
6727 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = GetBase()->GetEffect(1))
6728 manaFeedVal = aurEff->GetAmount();
6729 // Mana Feed - Drain Mana
6730 if (manaFeedVal > 0)
6731 {
6732 int32 feedAmount = CalculatePct(gainedAmount, manaFeedVal);
6733 caster->CastCustomSpell(caster, 32554, &feedAmount, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, this);
6734 }
6735 }
6736}
6737
6738void AuraEffect::HandleObsModPowerAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6739{
6740 Powers PowerType;
6741 if (GetMiscValue() == POWER_ALL)
6742 PowerType = target->getPowerType();
6743 else
6744 PowerType = Powers(GetMiscValue());
6745
6746 if (!target->IsAlive() || !target->GetMaxPower(PowerType))
6747 return;
6748
6749 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED))
6750 {
6751 SendTickImmune(target, caster);
6752 return;
6753 }
6754
6755 // don't regen when permanent aura target has full power
6756 if (GetBase()->IsPermanent() && target->GetPower(PowerType) == target->GetMaxPower(PowerType))
6757 return;
6758
6759 // ignore negative values (can be result apply spellmods to aura damage
6760 uint32 amount = std::max(m_amount, 0) * target->GetMaxPower(PowerType) / 100;
6761 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura.effect", "PeriodicTick: {} energize {} for {} dmg inflicted by {}",
6762 GetCasterGUID().ToString(), target->GetGUID().ToString(), amount, GetId());
6763 SpellPeriodicAuraLogInfo pInfo(this, amount, 0, 0, 0, 0.0f, false);
6764 target->SendPeriodicAuraLog(&pInfo);
6765
6766 int32 gain = target->ModifyPower(PowerType, amount);
6767
6768 if (caster)
6769 target->getHostileRefMgr().threatAssist(caster, float(gain) * 0.5f, GetSpellInfo());
6770}
6771
6772void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicEnergizeAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6773{
6774 Powers PowerType = Powers(GetMiscValue());
6775
6776 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && target->getPowerType() != PowerType && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR7_ONLY_IN_SPELLBOOK_UNTIL_LEARNED))
6777 return;
6778
6779 if (!target->IsAlive() || !target->GetMaxPower(PowerType))
6780 return;
6781
6782 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED))
6783 {
6784 SendTickImmune(target, caster);
6785 return;
6786 }
6787
6788 // don't regen when permanent aura target has full power
6789 if (GetBase()->IsPermanent() && target->GetPower(PowerType) == target->GetMaxPower(PowerType))
6790 return;
6791
6792 // ignore negative values (can be result apply spellmods to aura damage
6793 int32 amount = std::max(m_amount, 0);
6794
6795 SpellPeriodicAuraLogInfo pInfo(this, amount, 0, 0, 0, 0.0f, false);
6796 target->SendPeriodicAuraLog(&pInfo);
6797
6798 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura.effect", "PeriodicTick: {} energize {} for {} dmg inflicted by {}",
6799 GetCasterGUID().ToString(), target->GetGUID().ToString(), amount, GetId());
6800 int32 gain = target->ModifyPower(PowerType, amount);
6801
6802 if (caster)
6803 target->getHostileRefMgr().threatAssist(caster, float(gain) * 0.5f, GetSpellInfo());
6804}
6805
6806void AuraEffect::HandlePeriodicPowerBurnAuraTick(Unit* target, Unit* caster) const
6807{
6808 Powers PowerType = Powers(GetMiscValue());
6809
6810 if (!caster || !target->IsAlive() || target->getPowerType() != PowerType)
6811 return;
6812
6813 if (target->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED) || target->IsImmunedToDamageOrSchool(GetSpellInfo()))
6814 {
6815 SendTickImmune(target, caster);
6816 return;
6817 }
6818
6819 // ignore negative values (can be result apply spellmods to aura damage
6820 int32 damage = std::max(m_amount, 0);
6821
6822 // resilience reduce mana draining effect at spell crit damage reduction (added in 2.4)
6823 if (PowerType == POWER_MANA)
6824 damage -= target->GetSpellCritDamageReduction(damage);
6825
6826 uint32 gain = uint32(-target->ModifyPower(PowerType, -damage));
6827
6828 float dmgMultiplier = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].CalcValueMultiplier(caster);
6829
6830 SpellInfo const* spellProto = GetSpellInfo();
6831 // maybe has to be sent different to client, but not by SMSG_PERIODICAURALOG
6832 SpellNonMeleeDamage damageInfo(caster, target, spellProto, spellProto->SchoolMask);
6833 // no SpellDamageBonus for burn mana
6834 caster->CalculateSpellDamageTaken(&damageInfo, int32(gain * dmgMultiplier), spellProto);
6835
6836 Unit::DealDamageMods(damageInfo.target, damageInfo.damage, &damageInfo.absorb);
6837
6838 caster->SendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(&damageInfo);
6839
6840 // Set trigger flag
6841 uint32 procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_PERIODIC;
6842 uint32 procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_PERIODIC;
6843 uint32 procEx = createProcExtendMask(&damageInfo, SPELL_MISS_NONE) | PROC_EX_INTERNAL_DOT;
6844 if (damageInfo.damage)
6845 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_DAMAGE;
6846
6847 caster->DealSpellDamage(&damageInfo, true);
6848
6849 DamageInfo dmgInfo(damageInfo, DOT);
6850 Unit::ProcDamageAndSpell(caster, damageInfo.target, procAttacker, procVictim, procEx, damageInfo.damage, BASE_ATTACK, spellProto, nullptr, GetEffIndex(), nullptr, &dmgInfo);
6851}

6853void AuraEffect::HandleProcTriggerSpellAuraProc(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
6854{
6855 Unit* triggerCaster = aurApp->GetTarget();
6856 Unit* triggerTarget = eventInfo.GetProcTarget();
6857
6858 uint32 triggerSpellId = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].TriggerSpell;
6859 if (SpellInfo const* triggeredSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(triggerSpellId))
6860 {
6861 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandleProcTriggerSpellAuraProc: Triggering spell {} from aura {} proc", triggeredSpellInfo->Id, GetId());
6862 triggerCaster->CastSpell(triggerTarget, triggeredSpellInfo, true, nullptr, this);
6863 }
6864 else
6865 {
6866 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandleProcTriggerSpellAuraProc: Could not trigger spell {} from aura {} proc, because the spell does not have an entry in Spell.dbc.", triggerSpellId, GetId());
6867 }
6868}

6877 {
6878 // used only with EXTRA_LOGS

6880
6881 int32 basepoints0 = GetAmount();

6883 triggerCaster->CastCustomSpell(triggerTarget, triggerSpellId, &basepoints0, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, this);

6890
6891void AuraEffect::HandleProcTriggerDamageAuraProc(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
6892{
6893 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
6894 Unit* triggerTarget = eventInfo.GetProcTarget();
6895 if (triggerTarget->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED) || triggerTarget->IsImmunedToDamageOrSchool(GetSpellInfo()))
6896 {
6897 SendTickImmune(triggerTarget, target);
6898 return;
6899 }
6900
6901 SpellNonMeleeDamage damageInfo(target, triggerTarget, GetSpellInfo(), GetSpellInfo()->SchoolMask);
6902 uint32 damage = target->SpellDamageBonusDone(triggerTarget, GetSpellInfo(), GetAmount(), SPELL_DIRECT_DAMAGE, GetEffIndex());
6903 damage = triggerTarget->SpellDamageBonusTaken(target, GetSpellInfo(), damage, SPELL_DIRECT_DAMAGE);
6904 target->CalculateSpellDamageTaken(&damageInfo, damage, GetSpellInfo());
6905 Unit::DealDamageMods(damageInfo.target, damageInfo.damage, &damageInfo.absorb);
6906 target->SendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(&damageInfo);
6907 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandleProcTriggerDamageAuraProc: Triggering {} spell damage from aura {} proc", damage, GetId());
6908 target->DealSpellDamage(&damageInfo, true);
6909}
6910
6911void AuraEffect::HandleRaidProcFromChargeAuraProc(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& /*eventInfo*/)
6912{
6913 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
6914
6915 uint32 triggerSpellId;
6916 switch (GetId())
6917 {
6918 case 57949: // Shiver
6919 triggerSpellId = 57952;
6920 //animationSpellId = 57951; dummy effects for jump spell have unknown use (see also 41637)
6921 break;
6922 case 59978: // Shiver
6923 triggerSpellId = 59979;
6924 break;
6925 case 43593: // Cold Stare
6926 triggerSpellId = 43594;
6927 break;
6928 default:
6929 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandleRaidProcFromChargeAuraProc: received not handled spell: {}", GetId());
6930 return;
6931 }
6932
6933 int32 jumps = GetBase()->GetCharges();
6934
6935 // current aura expire on proc finish
6936 GetBase()->SetCharges(0);
6937 GetBase()->SetUsingCharges(true);
6938
6939 // next target selection
6940 if (jumps > 0)
6941 {
6942 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
6943 {
6944 float radius = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].CalcRadius(caster);
6945
6946 if (Unit* triggerTarget = target->GetNextRandomRaidMemberOrPet(radius))
6947 {
6948 target->CastSpell(triggerTarget, GetSpellInfo(), true, nullptr, this, GetCasterGUID());
6949 if (Aura* aura = triggerTarget->GetAura(GetId(), GetCasterGUID()))
6950 aura->SetCharges(jumps);
6951 }
6952 }
6953 }
6954
6955 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandleRaidProcFromChargeAuraProc: Triggering spell {} from aura {} proc", triggerSpellId, GetId());
6956 target->CastSpell(target, triggerSpellId, true, nullptr, this, GetCasterGUID());
6957}
6958
6959void AuraEffect::HandleRaidProcFromChargeWithValueAuraProc(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& /*eventInfo*/)
6960{
6961 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
6962
6963 // Currently only Prayer of Mending
6964 if (!(GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST && GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x20))
6965 {
6966 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandleRaidProcFromChargeWithValueAuraProc: received not handled spell: {}", GetId());
6967 return;
6968 }
6969 uint32 triggerSpellId = 33110;
6970
6971 int32 value = GetAmount();
6972
6973 int32 jumps = GetBase()->GetCharges();
6974
6975 // current aura expire on proc finish
6976 GetBase()->SetCharges(0);
6977 GetBase()->SetUsingCharges(true);
6978
6979 // next target selection
6980 if (jumps > 0)
6981 {
6982 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
6983 {
6984 float radius = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[GetEffIndex()].CalcRadius(caster);
6985
6986 Unit* triggerTarget = nullptr;
6987 Acore::MostHPMissingGroupInRange u_check(target, radius, 0);
6988 Acore::UnitLastSearcher<Acore::MostHPMissingGroupInRange> searcher(target, triggerTarget, u_check);
6989 Cell::VisitAllObjects(target, searcher, radius);
6990
6991 if (triggerTarget)
6992 {
6993 target->CastCustomSpell(triggerTarget, GetId(), &value, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, this, GetCasterGUID());
6994 if (Aura* aura = triggerTarget->GetAura(GetId(), GetCasterGUID()))
6995 aura->SetCharges(jumps);
6996 }
6997 }
6998 }
6999
7000 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "AuraEffect::HandleRaidProcFromChargeWithValueAuraProc: Triggering spell {} from aura {} proc", triggerSpellId, GetId());
7001 target->CastCustomSpell(target, triggerSpellId, &value, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, this, GetCasterGUID());
7002}
7003
7004int32 AuraEffect::GetTotalTicks() const
7005{
7006 uint32 totalTicks = 1;
7007 if (m_amplitude)
7008 {
7009 totalTicks = GetBase()->GetMaxDuration() / m_amplitude;
7010
7011 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_EXTRA_INITIAL_PERIOD))
7012 {
7013 ++totalTicks;
7014 }
7015 }
7016
7017 return totalTicks;
7018}
